natdex_data0001_bulbasaur.description:
Bulbasaur can be seen napping in bright
sunlight. There is a seed on its back.
By soaking up the sun's rays, the seed
grows progressively larger.\x
natdex_data0001_bulbasaur.name: Bulbasaur

natdex_data0002_ivysaur.description:
To support its bulb, Ivysaur's legs
grow sturdy. If it spends more time lying in
the sunlight, the bud will soon bloom into
a large flower.\x
natdex_data0002_ivysaur.name: Ivysaur

natdex_data0003_venusaur.description:
Venusaur's flower is said to take on vivid
colors if it gets plenty of nutrition and
sunlight. The flower's aroma soothes the
emotions of people.\x
natdex_data0003_venusaur.name: Venusaur

natdex_data0004_charmander.description:
The flame that burns at the tip of its
tail is an indication of its emotions.
The flame wavers when Charmander is
happy, and blazes when it is enraged.\x
natdex_data0004_charmander.name: Charmander

natdex_data0005_charmeleon.description:
Without pity, its sharp claws destroy foes.
If it encounters a strong enemy, it
becomes agitated, and the flame on its
tail flares with a bluish white color.\x
natdex_data0005_charmeleon.name: Charmeleon

natdex_data0006_charizard.description:
A Charizard flies about in search of
strong opponents. It breathes intense
flames that can melt any material. However,
it will never torch a weaker foe.\x
natdex_data0006_charizard.name: Charizard

natdex_data0007_squirtle.description:
Its shell is not just for protection.
Its rounded shape and the grooves on its
surface minimize resistance in water,
enabling Squirtle to swim at high speeds.\x
natdex_data0007_squirtle.name: Squirtle

natdex_data0008_wartortle.description:
Its large tail is covered with rich, thick
fur that deepens in color with age.
The scratches on its shell are evidence
of this Pokémon's toughness in battle.\x
natdex_data0008_wartortle.name: Wartortle

natdex_data0009_blastoise.description:
Its large tail is covered with rich, thick
fur that deepens in color with age.
The scratches on its shell are evidence
of this Pokémon's toughness in battle.\x
natdex_data0009_blastoise.name: Blastoise

natdex_data0010_caterpie.description:
Its voracious appetite compels it to
devour leaves bigger than itself without
hesitation. It releases a terribly strong
odor from its antennae.\x
natdex_data0010_caterpie.name: Caterpie

natdex_data0011_metapod.description:
Its shell is as hard as an iron slab.
A Metapod does not move very much
because it is preparing its soft innards
for evolution inside the shell.\x
natdex_data0011_metapod.name: Metapod

natdex_data0012_butterfree.description:
It has a superior ability to search for
delicious honey from flowers. It can seek,
extract, and carry honey from flowers
blooming over six miles away.\x
natdex_data0012_butterfree.name: Butterfree

natdex_data0013_weedle.description:
A Weedle has an extremely acute sense
of smell. It distinguishes its favorite
kinds of leaves from those it dislikes by
sniffing with its big red nose.\x
natdex_data0013_weedle.name: Weedle

natdex_data0014_kakuna.description:
It remains virtually immobile while it
clings to a tree. However, on the inside,
it busily prepares for evolution. This is
evident from how hot its shell becomes.\x
natdex_data0014_kakuna.name: Kakuna

natdex_data0015_beedrill.description:
A Beedrill is extremely territorial.
For safety reasons, no one should ever
approach its nest. If angered, they will
attack in a swarm.\x
natdex_data0015_beedrill.name: Beedrill

natdex_data0016_pidgey.description:
It has an extremely sharp sense of
direction. It can unerringly return home to
its nest, however far it may be removed
from its familiar surroundings.\x
natdex_data0016_pidgey.name: Pidgey

natdex_data0017_pidgeotto.description:
This Pokémon flies around, patrolling its
large territory. If its living space is
violated, it shows no mercy in thoroughly
punishing the foe with its sharp claws.\x
natdex_data0017_pidgeotto.name: Pidgeotto

natdex_data0018_pidgeot.description:
This Pokémon has gorgeous, glossy
feathers. Many Trainers are so captivated
by the beautiful feathers on its head that
they choose Pidgeot as their Pokémon.\x
natdex_data0018_pidgeot.name: Pidgeot

natdex_data0019_rattata.description:
A Rattata is cautious in the extreme.
Even while it is asleep, it constantly
moves its ears and listens for danger.
It will make its nest anywhere.\x
natdex_data0019_rattata.name: Rattata

natdex_data0020_raticate.description:
A Raticate's sturdy fangs grow steadily.
To keep them ground down, it gnaws on
rocks and logs. It may even chew on the
walls of houses.\x
natdex_data0020_raticate.name: Raticate

natdex_data0021_spearow.description:
Its loud cry can be heard over half a mile
away. If its high, keening cry is heard
echoing all around, it is a sign that they
are warning each other of danger.\x
natdex_data0021_spearow.name: Spearow

natdex_data0022_fearow.description:
Its long neck and elongated beak are
ideal for catching prey in soil or water.
It deftly moves this extended and skinny
beak to pluck prey.\x
natdex_data0022_fearow.name: Fearow

natdex_data0023_ekans.description:
An Ekans curls itself up in a spiral while
it rests. This position allows it to quickly
respond to an enemy from any direction
with a threat from its upraised head.\x
natdex_data0023_ekans.name: Ekans

natdex_data0024_arbok.description:
This Pokémon has a terrifically strong
constricting power. It can even flatten
steel oil drums. Once it wraps its body
around its foe, escaping is impossible.\x
natdex_data0024_arbok.name: Arbok

natdex_data0025_pikachu.description:
It stores electricity in the electric sacs
on its cheeks. When it releases pent-up
energy in a burst, the electric power is
equal to a lightning bolt.\x
natdex_data0025_pikachu.name: Pikachu

natdex_data0026_raichu.description:
If it stores too much electricity, its
behavior turns aggressive. To avoid this,
it occasionally discharges excess energy
and calms itself down.\x
natdex_data0026_raichu.name: Raichu

natdex_data0027_sandshrew.description:
When it curls up in a ball, it can make any
attack bounce off harmlessly. Its hide has
turned tough and solid as a result of
living in the desert.\x
natdex_data0027_sandshrew.name: Sandshrew

natdex_data0028_sandslash.description:
It curls up in a ball to protect itself from
enemy attacks. It also curls up to prevent
heatstroke during the daytime when
temperatures rise sharply.\x
natdex_data0028_sandslash.name: Sandslash

natdex_data0029_nidoran.description:
Its highly toxic barbs are thought to have
developed as protection for this small-
bodied Pokémon. When enraged, it releases
a horrible toxin from its horn.\x
natdex_data0029_nidoran.name: Nidoran?

natdex_data0030_nidorina.description:
When it is with its friends or
family, its barbs are tucked away to
prevent injury. It appears to become
nervous if separated from the others.\x
natdex_data0030_nidorina.name: Nidorina

natdex_data0031_nidoqueen.description:
It is adept at sending foes flying with
harsh tackles using its tough, scaly body.
This Pokémon is at its strongest when
it is defending its young.\x
natdex_data0031_nidoqueen.name: Nidoqueen

natdex_data0032_nidoran.description:
The male Nidoran has developed muscles
that freely move its ears in any direction.
Even the slightest sound does not escape
this Pokémon's notice.\x
natdex_data0032_nidoran.name: Nidoran?

natdex_data0033_nidorino.description:
Its horn is harder than a diamond.
If it senses a hostile presence, all the
barbs on its back bristle up at once, and it
challenges the foe with all its might.\x
natdex_data0033_nidorino.name: Nidorino

natdex_data0034_nidoking.description:
A Nidoking's thick tail packs enormously
destructive power capable of toppling
a metal transmission tower. Once it goes
on a rampage, there is no stopping it.\x
natdex_data0034_nidoking.name: Nidoking

natdex_data0035_clefairy.description:
On every night of a full moon, they come
out to play. When dawn arrives, the tired
Clefairy go to sleep nestled up against
each other in deep and quiet mountains.\x
natdex_data0035_clefairy.name: Clefairy

natdex_data0036_clefable.description:
A Clefable uses its wings to skip lightly 
as if it were flying. Its bouncy step
lets it even walk on water. On quiet,
moonlit nights, it strolls on lakes.\x
natdex_data0036_clefable.name: Clefable

natdex_data0037_vulpix.description:
It can freely control fire, making fiery
orbs fly like will-o'-the-wisps. Just
before evolution, its six tails grow hot 
as if on fire.\x
natdex_data0037_vulpix.name: Vulpix

natdex_data0038_ninetales.description:
It has long been said that each of the
nine tails embody an enchanted power.
A long-lived Ninetales will have fur that
shines like gold.\x
natdex_data0038_ninetales.name: Ninetales

natdex_data0039_jigglypuff.description:
Nothing can avoid falling asleep hearing a
Jigglypuff's song. The sound waves of its
singing voice match the brain waves of
someone in a deep sleep.\x
natdex_data0039_jigglypuff.name: Jigglypuff

natdex_data0040_wigglytuff.description:
Its fur is the ultimate in luxuriousness.
Sleeping alongside a Wigglytuff is simply
divine. Its body expands seemingly without
end when it inhales.\x
natdex_data0040_wigglytuff.name: Wigglytuff

natdex_data0041_zubat.description:
While living in pitch-black caverns, their
eyes gradually grew shut and deprived
them of vision. They use ultrasonic waves
to detect obstacles.\x
natdex_data0041_zubat.name: Zubat

natdex_data0042_golbat.description:
Its fangs easily puncture even thick
animal hide. It loves to feast on the blood
of people and Pokémon. It flits about in
darkness and strikes from behind.\x
natdex_data0042_golbat.name: Golbat

natdex_data0043_oddish.description:
This Pokémon grows by absorbing moonlight.
During the daytime, it buries itself in the
ground, leaving only its leaves exposed to
avoid detection by its enemies.\x
natdex_data0043_oddish.name: Oddish

natdex_data0044_gloom.description:
A horribly noxious honey drools from its
mouth. One whiff of the honey can result
in memory loss. Some fans are said to
enjoy this overwhelming stink, however.\x
natdex_data0044_gloom.name: Gloom

natdex_data0045_vileplume.description:
In seasons when it produces more pollen,
the air around a Vileplume turns yellow
with the powder as it walks. The pollen is
highly toxic and causes paralysis.\x
natdex_data0045_vileplume.name: Vileplume

natdex_data0046_paras.description:
A Paras has parasitic tochukaso
mushrooms growing on its back. They grow
by drawing nutrients from the host. They
are valued as a medicine for long life.\x
natdex_data0046_paras.name: Paras

natdex_data0047_parasect.description:
Parasect are known to infest the roots of
large trees en masse and drain nutrients.
When an infested tree dies, they move
onto another tree all at once.\x
natdex_data0047_parasect.name: Parasect

natdex_data0048_venonat.description:
Its coat of thin, stiff hair that covers
its entire body is said to have evolved
for protection. Its large eyes never fail
to spot even miniscule prey.\x
natdex_data0048_venonat.name: Venonat

natdex_data0049_venomoth.description:
Venomoth are nocturnal--they are only
active at night. Their favorite prey are
insects that gather around streetlights,
attracted by the light in the darkness.\x
natdex_data0049_venomoth.name: Venomoth

natdex_data0050_diglett.description:
Diglett are raised in most farms.
The reason is simple--wherever they
burrow, the soil is left perfectly tilled
for growing delicious crops.\x
natdex_data0050_diglett.name: Diglett

natdex_data0051_dugtrio.description:
Because the triplets originally split from
one body, they think exactly alike.
They work cooperatively to burrow
endlessly through the ground.\x
natdex_data0051_dugtrio.name: Dugtrio

natdex_data0052_meowth.description:
Meowth withdraw their sharp claws into
their paws to silently sneak about.
For some reason, this Pokémon loves
shiny coins that glitter with light.\x
natdex_data0052_meowth.name: Meowth

natdex_data0053_persian.description:
A Persian's six bold whiskers sense air
movements to determine what is in its
vicinity. It becomes docile if grabbed
by the whiskers.\x
natdex_data0053_persian.name: Persian

natdex_data0054_psyduck.description:
When its headache intensifies, it starts
using strange powers. However, it has no
recollection of its powers, so it always
looks befuddled and bewildered.\x
natdex_data0054_psyduck.name: Psyduck

natdex_data0055_golduck.description:
A Golduck is an adept swimmer.
It sometimes joins competitive swimmers
in training. It uses psychic powers when
its forehead shimmers with light.\x
natdex_data0055_golduck.name: Golduck

natdex_data0056_mankey.description:
When it starts shaking and its nasal
breathing turns rough, it's a sure sign
of anger. However, since this happens
instantly, there is no time to flee.\x
natdex_data0056_mankey.name: Mankey

natdex_data0057_primeape.description:
When it becomes furious, its blood
circulation becomes more robust, and
its muscles are made stronger. But it
also becomes much less intelligent.\x
natdex_data0057_primeape.name: Primeape

natdex_data0058_growlithe.description:
Its superb sense of smell ensures that
this Pokémon won't forget any scent,
no matter what. It uses its sense of smell
to detect the emotions of others.\x
natdex_data0058_growlithe.name: Growlithe

natdex_data0059_arcanine.description:
This fleet-footed Pokémon is said to run
over 6,200 miles in a single day and night.
The fire that blazes wildly within its body
is its source of power.\x
natdex_data0059_arcanine.name: Arcanine

natdex_data0060_poliwag.description:
It is possible to see this Pokémon's spiral
innards right through its thin skin.
However, the skin is also very flexible.
Even sharp fangs bounce right off it.\x
natdex_data0060_poliwag.name: Poliwag

natdex_data0061_poliwhirl.description:
Its body surface is always wet and slick
with an oily fluid. Because of this greasy
covering, it can easily slip and slide out
of the clutches of any enemy in battle.\x
natdex_data0061_poliwhirl.name: Poliwhirl

natdex_data0062_poliwrath.description:
Its highly developed muscles never grow
fatigued, however much it exercises.
This Pokémon can swim back and forth
across the Pacific Ocean without effort.\x
natdex_data0062_poliwrath.name: Poliwrath

natdex_data0063_abra.description:
A Pokémon that sleeps 18 hours a day.
Observation revealed that it uses
TELEPORT to change its location once
every hour.\x
natdex_data0063_abra.name: Abra

natdex_data0064_kadabra.description:
It is rumored that a boy with psychic
abilities suddenly transformed into
Kadabra while he was assisting research
into extrasensory powers.\x
natdex_data0064_kadabra.name: Kadabra

natdex_data0065_alakazam.description:
While it has strong psychic abilities and
high intelligence, an Alakazam's muscles
are very weak. It uses psychic power to
move its body.\x
natdex_data0065_alakazam.name: Alakazam

natdex_data0066_machop.description:
It continually undertakes strenuous
training to master all forms of martial
arts. Its strength lets it easily hoist
a sumo wrestler onto its shoulders.\x
natdex_data0066_machop.name: Machop

natdex_data0067_machoke.description:
A belt is worn by a Machoke to keep its
overwhelming power under control.
Because it is so dangerous, no one has
ever removed the belt.\x
natdex_data0067_machoke.name: Machoke

natdex_data0068_machamp.description:
It is impossible to defend against punches
and chops doled out by its four arms.
Its fighting spirit flares up when it faces
a tough opponent.\x
natdex_data0068_machamp.name: Machamp

natdex_data0069_bellsprout.description:
A Bellsprout's thin and flexible body lets
it bend and sway to avoid any attack,
however strong it may be. From its mouth,
it leaks a fluid that melts even iron.\x
natdex_data0069_bellsprout.name: Bellsprout

natdex_data0070_weepinbell.description:
At night, a Weepinbell hangs on to a tree
branch with its hooked rear and sleeps.
If it moves around in its sleep, it may
wake up to find itself on the ground.\x
natdex_data0070_weepinbell.name: Weepinbell

natdex_data0071_victreebel.description:
The long vine extending from its head is
waved about as if it were a living thing to
attract prey. When an unsuspecting victim
approaches, it is swallowed whole.\x
natdex_data0071_victreebel.name: Victreebel

natdex_data0072_tentacool.description:
Its body is almost entirely composed of
water. It ensnares its foe with its two
long tentacles, then stabs with the poison
stingers at their tips.\x
natdex_data0072_tentacool.name: Tentacool

natdex_data0073_tentacruel.description:
It lives in complex rock formations on
the ocean floor and traps prey using its
80 tentacles. Its red orbs glow when it
grows excited or agitated.\x
natdex_data0073_tentacruel.name: Tentacruel

natdex_data0074_geodude.description:
It climbs mountain paths using only the
power of its arms. Because they look just
like boulders lining paths, hikers may step
on them without noticing.\x
natdex_data0074_geodude.name: Geodude

natdex_data0075_graveler.description:
They descend from mountains by tumbling
down steep slopes. They are so brutal,
they smash aside obstructing trees and
massive boulders with thunderous tackles.\x
natdex_data0075_graveler.name: Graveler

natdex_data0076_golem.description:
It is said to live in volcanic craters
on mountain peaks. Once a year, it sheds
its hide and grows larger. The shed hide
crumbles and returns to the soil.\x
natdex_data0076_golem.name: Golem

natdex_data0077_ponyta.description:
A Ponyta is very weak at birth. It can
barely stand up. Its legs become stronger
as it stumbles and falls while trying to
keep up with its parent.\x
natdex_data0077_ponyta.name: Ponyta

natdex_data0078_rapidash.description:
It usually canters casually in the fields
and plains. But once a Rapidash turns
serious, its fiery manes flare and blaze
as it gallops its way up to 150 mph.\x
natdex_data0078_rapidash.name: Rapidash

natdex_data0079_slowpoke.description:
It catches prey by dipping its tail in
water at the side of a river. But it often
forgets what it is doing and spends entire
days just loafing at water's edge.\x
natdex_data0079_slowpoke.name: Slowpoke

natdex_data0080_slowbro.description:
Its tail has a Shellder firmly attached
with a bite. As a result, the tail can't be
used for fishing anymore. This forces it
to reluctantly swim and catch prey.\x
natdex_data0080_slowbro.name: Slowbro

natdex_data0100_voltorb.description:
It bears an uncanny and unexplained
resemblance to a Poké Ball. Because it
explodes at the slightest shock, even
veteran Trainers treat it with caution.\x
natdex_data0100_voltorb.name: Voltorb

natdex_data0101_electrode.description:
They appear in great numbers at electric
power plants. Because they feed on
electricity, they cause massive and
chaotic blackouts in nearby cities.\x
natdex_data0101_electrode.name: Electrode

natdex_data0102_exeggcute.description:
It consists of six eggs that care for each
other. The eggs attract each other and
spin around. When cracks increasingly
appear, it is close to evolution.\x
natdex_data0102_exeggcute.name: Exeggcute

natdex_data0103_exeggutor.description:
Originally from the tropics, Exeggutor's
heads grow larger from exposure to strong
sunlight. It is said that when the heads
fall, they group to form an Exeggcute.\x
natdex_data0103_exeggutor.name: Exeggutor

natdex_data0104_cubone.description:
It pines for the mother it will never see
again. Seeing a likeness of its mother in
the full moon, it cries. The stains on the
skull it wears are from its tears.\x
natdex_data0104_cubone.name: Cubone

natdex_data0105_marowak.description:
A Marowak is the evolved form of a Cubone
that has grown tough by overcoming the
grief of losing its mother. Its tempered
and hardened spirit is not easily broken.\x
natdex_data0105_marowak.name: Marowak

natdex_data0106_hitmonlee.description:
Its legs freely stretch and contract.
Using these springlike limbs, it bowls over
foes with devastating kicks. After battle,
it rubs down its tired legs.\x
natdex_data0106_hitmonlee.name: Hitmonlee

natdex_data0107_hitmonchan.description:
A Hitmonchan is said to possess the
spirit of a boxer who aimed to become the
world champion. Having an indomitable
spirit means that it will never give up.\x
natdex_data0107_hitmonchan.name: Hitmonchan

natdex_data0108_lickitung.description:
Whenever it sees something unfamiliar,
it always licks the object because it
memorizes things by texture and taste.
It is somewhat put off by sour things.\x
natdex_data0108_lickitung.name: Lickitung

natdex_data0109_koffing.description:
Getting up close to a Koffing will give
you a chance to observe, through its thin
skin, the toxic gases swirling inside. It
blows up at the slightest stimulation.\x
natdex_data0109_koffing.name: Koffing

natdex_data0110_weezing.description:
By diluting its toxic gases with a special
process, the highest grade of perfume can
be extracted. To Weezing, gases emanating
from garbage are the ultimate feast.\x
natdex_data0110_weezing.name: Weezing

natdex_data0111_rhyhorn.description:
Once it starts running, it doesn't stop.
Its tiny brain makes it so stupid that it
can't remember why it started running in
the first place.\x
natdex_data0111_rhyhorn.name: Rhyhorn

natdex_data0112_rhydon.description:
Its horn, which rotates like a drill,
destroys tall buildings with one strike.
It stands on its hind legs, and its brain
is well developed.\x
natdex_data0112_rhydon.name: Rhydon

natdex_data0113_chansey.description:
Chansey lay nutritionally excellent eggs
every day. The eggs are so delicious, they
are eagerly devoured by even those people
who have lost their appetite.\x
natdex_data0113_chansey.name: Chansey

natdex_data0114_tangela.description:
Its vines snap off easily and painlessly
if they are grabbed, allowing it to make a
quick getaway. The lost vines are replaced
by new growth the very next day.\x
natdex_data0114_tangela.name: Tangela

natdex_data0115_kangaskhan.description:
If you come across a young Kangaskhan
playing by itself, never try to catch it.
The baby's parent is sure to be in the area,
and it will become violently enraged.\x
natdex_data0115_kangaskhan.name: Kangaskhan

natdex_data0116_horsea.description:
By cleverly flicking the fins on its back
side to side, it moves in any direction
while facing forward. It spits ink to
escape if it senses danger.\x
natdex_data0116_horsea.name: Horsea

natdex_data0117_seadra.description:
The poisonous barbs all over its body are
highly valued as ingredients for making
traditional herbal medicine. It shows no
mercy to anything approaching its nest.\x
natdex_data0117_seadra.name: Seadra

natdex_data0118_goldeen.description:
In the springtime, schools of Goldeen
can be seen swimming up falls and rivers.
It metes out staggering damage with its
single horn.\x
natdex_data0118_goldeen.name: Goldeen

natdex_data0119_seaking.description:
It punches holes in boulders on stream-
beds. This is a clever innovation that
prevents its eggs from being attacked or
washed away by the current.\x
natdex_data0119_seaking.name: Seaking

natdex_data0120_staryu.description:
It gathers with others in the night and
makes its red core glow on and off with
the twinkling stars. It can regenerate
limbs if they are severed from its body.\x
natdex_data0120_staryu.name: Staryu

natdex_data0121_starmie.description:
People in ancient times imagined that
Starmie were transformed from the
reflections of stars that twinkled on
gentle waves at night.\x
natdex_data0121_starmie.name: Starmie

natdex_data0122_mrmime.description:
A Mr. Mime is a master of pantomime. It can
convince others that something unseeable
actually exists. Once believed, the
imaginary object does become real.\x
natdex_data0122_mrmime.name: Mr. Mime

natdex_data0123_scyther.description:
Its blindingly fast speed adds to the
sharpness of its twin forearm scythes.
The scythes can slice through thick logs
in one wicked stroke.\x
natdex_data0123_scyther.name: Scyther

natdex_data0124_jynx.description:
A JYNX sashays rhythmically as if it were
dancing. Its motions are so bouncingly
alluring, people seeing it are compelled to
shake their hips without noticing.\x
natdex_data0124_jynx.name: Jynx

natdex_data0125_electabuzz.description:
When a storm approaches, it competes with
others to scale heights that are likely to
be stricken by lightning. Some towns use
Electabuzz in place of lightning rods.\x
natdex_data0125_electabuzz.name: Electabuzz

natdex_data0126_magmar.description:
In battle, it blows out intense flames from
all over its body to intimidate its foe.
These fiery bursts create heat waves that
ignite grass and trees in the area.\x
natdex_data0126_magmar.name: Magmar

natdex_data0127_pinsir.description:
Their pincers are strong enough to
shatter thick logs. Because they dislike
cold, Pinsir burrow and sleep under
the ground on chilly nights.\x
natdex_data0127_pinsir.name: Pinsir

natdex_data0128_tauros.description:
It is not satisfied unless it is rampaging
at all times. If there is no opponent for
Tauros to battle, it will charge at thick
trees and knock them down to calm itself.\x
natdex_data0128_tauros.name: Tauros

natdex_data0129_magikarp.description:
Its swimming muscles are weak, so it is
easily washed away by currents. In places
where water pools, you can see many
Magikarp deposited there by the flow.\x
natdex_data0129_magikarp.name: Magikarp

natdex_data0130_gyarados.description:
It is an extremely vicious and violent
Pokémon. When humans begin to fight,
it will appear and burn everything to the
ground with intensely hot flames.\x
natdex_data0130_gyarados.name: Gyarados

natdex_data0131_lapras.description:
People have driven Lapras almost to the
point of extinction. In the evenings,
it is said to sing plaintively as it seeks
what few others of its kind still remain.\x
natdex_data0131_lapras.name: Lapras

natdex_data0132_ditto.description:
A Ditto rearranges its cell structure to
transform itself. However, if it tries to
change based on its memory, it will get
details wrong.\x
natdex_data0132_ditto.name: Ditto

natdex_data0133_eevee.description:
An Eevee has an unstable genetic makeup
that suddenly mutates due to its
environment. Radiation from various
StoneS causes this Pokémon to evolve.\x
natdex_data0133_eevee.name: Eevee

natdex_data0134_vaporeon.description:
Vaporeon underwent a spontaneous
mutation and grew fins and gills that
allow them to live underwater. They have
the ability to freely control water.\x
natdex_data0134_vaporeon.name: Vaporeon

natdex_data0135_jolteon.description:
Its cells generate weak power that is
amplified by its fur's static electricity
to drop thunderbolts. The bristling fur is
made of electrically charged needles.\x
natdex_data0135_jolteon.name: Jolteon

natdex_data0136_flareon.description:
Flareon's fluffy fur releases heat into
the air so that its body does not get
excessively hot. Its body temperature can
rise to a maximum of 1,650 degrees F.\x
natdex_data0136_flareon.name: Flareon

natdex_data0137_porygon.description:
It is capable of reverting itself entirely
back to program data in order to enter
cyberspace. A Porygon is copy-
protected so it cannot be duplicated.\x
natdex_data0137_porygon.name: Porygon

natdex_data0138_omanyte.description:
One of the ancient and long-since-extinct
Pokémon that have been regenerated
from fossils by humans. If attacked,
it withdraws into its hard shell.\x
natdex_data0138_omanyte.name: Omanyte

natdex_data0139_omastar.description:
An Omastar uses its tentacles to capture
its prey. It is believed to have become
extinct because its shell grew too large,
making its movements slow and ponderous.\x
natdex_data0139_omastar.name: Omastar

natdex_data0140_kabuto.description:
It is a Pokémon that has been regenerated
from a fossil. However, in rare cases, living
examples have been discovered. Kabuto
have not changed for 300 million years.\x
natdex_data0140_kabuto.name: Kabuto

natdex_data0141_kabutops.description:
Kabutops once swam underwater to hunt 
for prey. It was apparently evolving from
being a water dweller to living on land as
evident from changes in its gills and legs.\x
natdex_data0141_kabutops.name: Kabutops

natdex_data0142_aerodactyl.description:
Aerodactyl is a Pokémon from the age
of dinosaurs. It was regenerated from DNA
extracted from amber. It is imagined to
have been the king of the skies.\x
natdex_data0142_aerodactyl.name: Aerodactyl

natdex_data0143_snorlax.description:
Snorlax's typical day consists of nothing
more than eating and sleeping. It is such
a docile Pokémon that there are children
who use its big belly as a place to play.\x
natdex_data0143_snorlax.name: Snorlax

natdex_data0144_articuno.description:
Articuno is a legendary bird Pokémon that
can control ice. The flapping of its wings
chills the air. As a result, it is said that
when this Pokémon flies, snow will fall.\x
natdex_data0144_articuno.name: Articuno

natdex_data0145_zapdos.description:
Zapdos is a legendary bird Pokémon that
has the ability to control electricity.
It usually lives in thunderclouds. It gains
power if it is stricken by lightning bolts.\x
natdex_data0145_zapdos.name: Zapdos

natdex_data0146_moltres.description:
Moltres is a legendary bird Pokémon
that can control fire. If injured, it is said
to dip its body in the molten magma of
a volcano to burn and heal itself.\x
natdex_data0146_moltres.name: Moltres

natdex_data0147_dratini.description:
A Dratini continually molts and sloughs
off its old skin. It does so because the
life energy within its body steadily builds
to reach uncontrollable levels.\x
natdex_data0147_dratini.name: Dratini

natdex_data0148_dragonair.description:
A Dragonair stores an enormous amount of
energy inside its body. It is said to alter
the weather around it by loosing energy
from the crystals on its neck and tail.\x
natdex_data0148_dragonair.name: Dragonair

natdex_data0149_dragonite.description:
It can circle the globe in just 16 hours.
It is a kindhearted Pokémon that leads
lost and foundering ships in a storm
to the safety of land.\x
natdex_data0149_dragonite.name: Dragonite

natdex_data0150_mewtwo.description:
A Pokémon that was created by genetic
manipulation. However, even though the
scientific power of humans made its body,
they failed to give it a warm heart.\x
natdex_data0150_mewtwo.name: Mewtwo

natdex_data0151_mew.description:
A MEW is said to possess the genes of all
Pokémon. It is capable of making itself
invisible at will, so it entirely avoids
notice even if it approaches people.\x
natdex_data0151_mew.name: Mew

natdex_data0152_chikorita.description:
It waves its leaf around to keep foes
at bay. However, a sweet fragrance also
wafts from the leaf, creating a friendly
atmosphere that becalms the battlers.\x
natdex_data0152_chikorita.name: Chikorita

natdex_data0153_bayleef.description:
A Bayleef's neck is ringed by curled-up
leaves. Inside each leaf is a small tree
shoot. The fragrance of this shoot
makes people peppy.\x
natdex_data0153_bayleef.name: Bayleef

natdex_data0154_meganium.description:
The fragrance of a Meganium's flower
soothes and calms emotions. In battle,
it gives off more of its becalming scent
to blunt the foe's fighting spirit.\x
natdex_data0154_meganium.name: Meganium

natdex_data0155_cyndaquil.description:
It flares flames from its back to protect
itself. The fire burns vigorously if the
Pokémon is angry. When it is tired,
it sputters with incomplete combustion.\x
natdex_data0155_cyndaquil.name: Cyndaquil

natdex_data0156_quilava.description:
It intimidates foes with intense gusts of
flames and superheated air. Its quick
nimbleness lets it dodge attacks even
while scorching an enemy.\x
natdex_data0156_quilava.name: Quilava

natdex_data0157_typhlosion.description:
It can hide behind a shimmering heat haze
that it creates using its intense flames.
Typhlosion create blazing explosive
blasts that burn everything to cinders.\x
natdex_data0157_typhlosion.name: Typhlosion

natdex_data0158_totodile.description:
Despite its small body, Totodile's jaws
are very powerful. While it may think it is
just playfully nipping, its bite has enough
strength to cause serious injury.\x
natdex_data0158_totodile.name: Totodile

natdex_data0159_croconaw.description:
Once its jaws clamp down on its foe, it will
absolutely not let go. Because the tips of
its fangs are forked back like fishhooks,
they become irremovably embedded.\x
natdex_data0159_croconaw.name: Croconaw

natdex_data0160_feraligatr.description:
It opens its huge mouth to intimidate
enemies. In battle, it runs using its thick
and powerful hind legs to charge the
foe with incredible speed.\x
natdex_data0160_feraligatr.name: Feraligatr

natdex_data0161_sentret.description:
They take turns standing guard when it
is time to sleep. The sentry awakens the
others if it senses danger. If one becomes
separated, it turns sleepless with fear.\x
natdex_data0161_sentret.name: Sentret

natdex_data0162_furret.description:
A Furret has a very slim build. When under
attack, it can squirm through narrow
spaces and get away. In spite of its short
limbs, it is very nimble and fleet.\x
natdex_data0162_furret.name: Furret

natdex_data0163_hoothoot.description:
It has an internal organ that senses
the earth's rotation. Using this special
organ, a Hoothoot begins hooting at
precisely the same time every day.\x
natdex_data0163_hoothoot.name: Hoothoot

natdex_data0164_noctowl.description:
It unfailingly catches prey in darkness.
Noctowl owe their success to superior
vision that allows them to see in minimal
light, and to their supple and silent wings.\x
natdex_data0164_noctowl.name: Noctowl

natdex_data0165_ledyba.description:
Ledyba communicate using a fluid that
they secrete from where the legs join the
body. They are said to convey feelings to
others by altering the fluid's scent.\x
natdex_data0165_ledyba.name: Ledyba

natdex_data0166_ledian.description:
It is said that in lands with clean air,
where the stars fill the sky, there live
many Ledian. For good reason, they use
the light of the stars as energy.\x
natdex_data0166_ledian.name: Ledian

natdex_data0167_spinarak.description:
The web it spins can be considered its
second nervous system. It is said that a
Spinarak determines its prey by the tiny
vibrations it feels through the web.\x
natdex_data0167_spinarak.name: Spinarak

natdex_data0168_ariados.description:
Its feet are tipped with tiny hooked claws
that enable it to scuttle on ceilings and
vertical walls. It constricts its foe with
thin and strong silk webbing.\x
natdex_data0168_ariados.name: Ariados

natdex_data0169_crobat.description:
Over the course of evolution, its hind legs
turned into wings. By alternately resting
its front and rear wings, it can fly all day
without having to stop.\x
natdex_data0169_crobat.name: Crobat

natdex_data0170_chinchou.description:
When it senses danger, it discharges
positive and negative electricity from its
two antennae. It lives in depths beyond
sunlight's reach.\x
natdex_data0170_chinchou.name: Chinchou

natdex_data0171_lanturn.description:
The light-emitting orbs on its back are
very bright. They are formed from a part of
its dorsal fin. This Pokémon illuminates
the inky darkness of deep seas.\x
natdex_data0171_lanturn.name: Lanturn

natdex_data0172_pichu.description:
It is still inept at retaining electricity.
When it is startled, it discharges power
accidentally. It gets better at holding
power as it grows older.\x
natdex_data0172_pichu.name: Pichu

natdex_data0173_cleffa.description:
On nights with many shooting stars,
Cleffa can be seen dancing in a ring.
They dance until daybreak, when they
quench their thirst with the morning dew.\x
natdex_data0173_cleffa.name: Cleffa

natdex_data0174_igglybuff.description:
Its soft and pliable body is very bouncy.
When it sings continuously with all its
might, its body steadily turns a deepening
pink color.\x
natdex_data0174_igglybuff.name: Igglybuff

natdex_data0175_togepi.description:
As its energy, it uses the feelings of
compassion and pleasure exuded by
people and Pokémon. It stores up happy
feelings in its shell, then shares them out.\x
natdex_data0175_togepi.name: Togepi

natdex_data0176_togetic.description:
It is said to be a Pokémon that brings good
fortune. When it spots someone who is pure
of heart, a Togetic appears and shares its
happiness with that person.\x
natdex_data0176_togetic.name: Togetic

natdex_data0177_natu.description:
It runs up short trees that grow on the
savanna to peck at new shoots.
A Natu's eyes look as if they are
always observing something.\x
natdex_data0177_natu.name: Natu

natdex_data0178_xatu.description:
It has the enigmatic power of foreseeing
the future. Some people in different lands
have long believed that XATU are
emissaries from another world.\x
natdex_data0178_xatu.name: Xatu

natdex_data0179_mareep.description:
Its fluffy wool rubs together and builds
a static charge. The more energy is
charged, the more brightly the lightbulb
at the tip of its tail glows.\x
natdex_data0179_mareep.name: Mareep

natdex_data0180_flaaffy.description:
Its fleece quality changes to generate
strong static electricity with a small
amount of wool. The bare, slick parts of its
hide are shielded against electricity.\x
natdex_data0180_flaaffy.name: Flaaffy

natdex_data0181_ampharos.description:
It gives off so much light that it can be
seen even from space. People in the old
days used its light to send signals back
and forth with others far away.\x
natdex_data0181_ampharos.name: Ampharos

natdex_data0182_bellossom.description:
Its flower petals deepen in color through
exposure to sunlight. When cloudy weather
persists, it does a dance that is thought
to be a ritual for summoning the sun.\x
natdex_data0182_bellossom.name: Bellossom

natdex_data0183_marill.description:
Its body is covered with water-repellent
fur. Because of the fur, it can swim
through water at high speed without being
slowed by the water's resistance.\x
natdex_data0183_marill.name: Marill

natdex_data0184_azumarill.description:
It lives in water virtually all day long.
Its body color and pattern act as
camouflage that makes it tough for
enemies to spot in water.\x
natdex_data0184_azumarill.name: Azumarill

natdex_data0185_sudowoodo.description:
It mimics a tree to avoid being attacked
by enemies. But since its forelegs
remain green throughout the year, it is
easily identified as a fake in the winter.\x
natdex_data0185_sudowoodo.name: Sudowoodo

natdex_data0186_politoed.description:
The curled hair on its head proves its
status as a king. It is said that the
longer and curlier the hair, the more
respect it earns from its peers.\x
natdex_data0186_politoed.name: Politoed

natdex_data0187_hoppip.description:
This Pokémon drifts and floats with the
wind. If it senses the approach of strong
winds, a Hoppip links leaves with others
to prepare against being blown away.\x
natdex_data0187_hoppip.name: Hoppip

natdex_data0188_skiploom.description:
It blossoms when the temperature rises
above 64 degrees F. Because its flower's
blooming changes with the temperature,
it is sometimes used as a thermometer.\x
natdex_data0188_skiploom.name: Skiploom

natdex_data0189_jumpluff.description:
Jumpluff ride warm southern winds to
cross the sea and fly to foreign lands.
This Pokémon lands when it encounters
cold air while it is floating.\x
natdex_data0189_jumpluff.name: Jumpluff

natdex_data0190_aipom.description:
Its tail ends with a dexterous, handlike
appendage. However, because it uses the
tail so much, Aipom's real hands have
become rather clumsy.\x
natdex_data0190_aipom.name: Aipom

natdex_data0191_sunkern.description:
Sunkern try to minimize movement to
conserve the nutrients they have stored
in their bodies for evolution. They will
not eat, subsisting only on morning dew.\x
natdex_data0191_sunkern.name: Sunkern

natdex_data0192_sunflora.description:
Sunflora convert solar energy into
nutrition. They are highly active in the
warm daytime but suddenly stop moving as
soon as the sun sets.\x
natdex_data0192_sunflora.name: Sunflora

natdex_data0193_yanma.description:
It can see 360 degrees without moving
its eyes. It is a great flier capable of
making sudden stops and turning midair to
quickly chase down targeted prey.\x
natdex_data0193_yanma.name: Yanma

natdex_data0194_wooper.description:
Wooper usually live in water but come
out onto land seeking food occasionally.
On land, they coat their bodies with a
gooey, toxic film.\x
natdex_data0194_wooper.name: Wooper

natdex_data0195_quagsire.description:
A Quagsire hunts by leaving its mouth wide
open in water and waiting for its prey to
blunder in. Because it doesn't move, it
does not get very hungry.\x
natdex_data0195_quagsire.name: Quagsire

natdex_data0196_espeon.description:
An Espeon is extremely loyal to any
Trainer it considers to be worthy. It is
said to have developed precognitive
powers to protect its Trainer from harm.\x
natdex_data0196_espeon.name: Espeon

natdex_data0197_umbreon.description:
Umbreon evolved from exposure to the
moon's energy pulses. It lurks in darkness
and waits for its foes to move. The rings
on its body glow when it leaps to attack.\x
natdex_data0197_umbreon.name: Umbreon

natdex_data0198_murkrow.description:
Murkrow were feared as the alleged
bearers of ill fortune. It shows strong
interest in anything that sparkles. It will
even try to steal rings from women.\x
natdex_data0198_murkrow.name: Murkrow

natdex_data0199_slowking.description:
It undertakes research every day to
solve the mysteries of the world.
However, it apparently forgets everything
if the Shellder on its head comes off.\x
natdex_data0199_slowking.name: Slowking

natdex_data0200_misdreavus.description:
A Misdreavus frightens people with a
creepy, sobbing cry. It apparently uses
its red spheres to absorb the fear of foes
as its nutrition.\x
natdex_data0200_misdreavus.name: Misdreavus

natdex_data0201_unown.description:
This Pokémon is shaped like ancient text
characters. Although research is ongoing,
it is a mystery as to which came first,
the ancient writings or the various Unown.\x
natdex_data0201_unown.name: Unown

natdex_data0202_wobbuffet.description:
Usually docile, a Wobbuffet strikes back
ferociously if its black tail is attacked.
It makes its lair in caves where it waits
for nightfall.\x
natdex_data0202_wobbuffet.name: Wobbuffet

natdex_data0203_girafarig.description:
A Girafarig is an herbivore--it eats
grass and tree shoots. While it is eating,
its tail makes chewing and swallowing
motions as if it were also eating.\x
natdex_data0203_girafarig.name: Girafarig

natdex_data0204_pineco.description:
A Pineco hangs from a tree branch and
waits for prey. While eating, if it is
disturbed by someone shaking its tree, it
falls on the ground and suddenly explodes.\x
natdex_data0204_pineco.name: Pineco

natdex_data0205_forretress.description:
It keeps itself inside its steel shell.
The shell is opened when it is catching
prey, but it is so quick that the shell's
inside cannot be seen.\x
natdex_data0205_forretress.name: Forretress

natdex_data0206_dunsparce.description:
Its drill-tipped tail is used to burrow into
the ground backwards. This Pokémon is
known to make its nest in complex shapes
deep under the ground.\x
natdex_data0206_dunsparce.name: Dunsparce

natdex_data0207_gligar.description:
It glides without making a single sound.
It grasps the face of its foe using its
hind and large front claws, then stabs
with its poison barb.\x
natdex_data0207_gligar.name: Gligar

natdex_data0208_steelix.description:
Steelix live even further underground
than Onix. This Pokémon is known to dig
toward the earth's core, reaching a depth
of over six-tenths of a mile underground.\x
natdex_data0208_steelix.name: Steelix

natdex_data0209_snubbull.description:
By baring its fangs and making a scary
face, it sends smaller Pokémon scurrying
in terror. The Snubbull does seem a
little sad at making its foes flee.\x
natdex_data0209_snubbull.name: Snubbull

natdex_data0210_granbull.description:
It has a particularly well-developed lower
jaw. The huge fangs are heavy, causing
it to tilt its head. Unless it is startled,
it will not try to bite.\x
natdex_data0210_granbull.name: Granbull

natdex_data0211_qwilfish.description:
A Qwilfish uses the pressure of water
it swallows to shoot toxic quills all at
once from all over its body. It finds
swimming to be somewhat challenging.\x
natdex_data0211_qwilfish.name: Qwilfish

natdex_data0212_scizor.description:
A Scizor has a body with the hardness of
steel. It is not easily fazed by ordinary
sorts of attacks. It flaps its wings to
regulate its body temperature.\x
natdex_data0212_scizor.name: Scizor

natdex_data0213_shuckle.description:
A Shuckle hides under rocks, keeping its
body concealed inside its shell while
eating stored berries. The berries mix with
its body fluids to become a juice.\x
natdex_data0213_shuckle.name: Shuckle

natdex_data0214_heracross.description:
They gather in forests seeking the sweet
sap of trees. It is completely clad in a
steel-hard shell. It is proud of its horn,
which it uses to fling foes.\x
natdex_data0214_heracross.name: Heracross

natdex_data0215_sneasel.description:
A Sneasel scales trees by punching its
hooked claws into the bark. It seeks out
unguarded nests and steals eggs for food
while the parents are away.\x
natdex_data0215_sneasel.name: Sneasel

natdex_data0216_teddiursa.description:
It licks its palms that are sweetened by
being soaked in honey. A Teddiursa makes
its own honey by blending fruits and pollen
collected by Beedrill.\x
natdex_data0216_teddiursa.name: Teddiursa

natdex_data0217_ursaring.description:
In forests, it is said that there are many
streams and towering trees where an
Ursaring gathers food. It walks through
its forest collecting food every day.\x
natdex_data0217_ursaring.name: Ursaring

natdex_data0218_slugma.description:
It is a species of Pokémon that lives in
volcanic areas. If its body cools, its skin
hardens and immobilizes it. To avoid that,
it sleeps near magma.\x
natdex_data0218_slugma.name: Slugma

natdex_data0219_magcargo.description:
The shell on its back is made of hardened
magma. Tens of thousands of years spent
living in volcanic craters have turned
Magcargo's bodies into magma.\x
natdex_data0219_magcargo.name: Magcargo

natdex_data0220_swinub.description:
It roots for food by rubbing its snout
against the ground. Its favorite food is a
mushroom that grows under dried grass.
It occasionally roots out hot springs.\x
natdex_data0220_swinub.name: Swinub

natdex_data0221_piloswine.description:
A Piloswine is covered by a thick coat
of long hair for enduring freezing cold.
It uses its tusks to dig up food that has
been buried under ice.\x
natdex_data0221_piloswine.name: Piloswine

natdex_data0222_corsola.description:
Corsola live in warm southern seas.
If the sea becomes polluted, the beautiful
coral stalks become discolored and crumble
away in tatters.\x
natdex_data0222_corsola.name: Corsola

natdex_data0223_remoraid.description:
A Remoraid uses its abdominal muscles
to forcefully expel swallowed water, then
shoot down flying prey. When evolution
approaches, it travels down rivers.\x
natdex_data0223_remoraid.name: Remoraid

natdex_data0224_octillery.description:
It ensnares its foe with its suction-
cupped tentacles before delivering the
finishing blow. If the foe turns out to be
too strong, it spews ink to escape.\x
natdex_data0224_octillery.name: Octillery

natdex_data0225_delibird.description:
It carries food bundled up in its tail.
There was a famous explorer who
managed to scale Mt. Everest thanks
to a Delibird sharing its food.\x
natdex_data0225_delibird.name: Delibird

natdex_data0226_mantine.description:
On sunny days, schools of Mantine can be
seen elegantly leaping over the waves.
It is not bothered by the Remoraid that
hitches rides.\x
natdex_data0226_mantine.name: Mantine

natdex_data0227_skarmory.description:
A Pokémon that has a body and wings of
steel. People in the past used feathers
fallen from Skarmory to make swords and
knives.\x
natdex_data0227_skarmory.name: Skarmory

natdex_data0228_houndour.description:
Houndour communicate with each other
using a variety of cries to corner their
prey. This Pokémon's remarkable teamwork
is simply unparalleled.\x
natdex_data0228_houndour.name: Houndour

natdex_data0229_houndoom.description:
In a Houndoom pack, the one with its horns
raked sharply back serves a leadership
role. They choose their leader by fighting
among themselves.\x
natdex_data0229_houndoom.name: Houndoom

natdex_data0230_kingdra.description:
It sleeps quietly, deep on the seafloor.
When it comes up to the surface, it
creates a huge whirlpool that can swallow
even ships.\x
natdex_data0230_kingdra.name: Kingdra

natdex_data0231_phanpy.description:
Phanpy's big ears serve as broad fans.
When it becomes hot, it flaps the ears
busily to cool down. Even the young are
very strong.\x
natdex_data0231_phanpy.name: Phanpy

natdex_data0232_donphan.description:
A Donphan is so strong it can easily haul
a dump truck. Its hide has toughened to a
rock-hard state. An ordinary sort of
attack won't even leave a scratch.\x
natdex_data0232_donphan.name: Donphan

natdex_data0233_porygon2.description:
It was created by humans using the power
of science. It has been given artificial
intelligence that enables it to learn new
gestures and emotions on its own.\x
natdex_data0233_porygon2.name: Porygon2

natdex_data0234_stantler.description:
Stantler's magnificent antlers were
once traded at high prices as works of art.
As a result, this Pokémon was hunted
close to extinction.\x
natdex_data0234_stantler.name: Stantler

natdex_data0235_smeargle.description:
A Smeargle marks its territory using a
fluid that leaks out from the tip of its
tail. About 5,000 different marks left by
this Pokémon have been found.\x
natdex_data0235_smeargle.name: Smeargle

natdex_data0236_tyrogue.description:
Tyrogue become stressed out if they do
not get to train every day. When raising
this Pokémon, the Trainer must establish
a regular training schedule.\x
natdex_data0236_tyrogue.name: Tyrogue

natdex_data0237_hitmontop.description:
Its technique of kicking while spinning is
a remarkable mix of both offense and
defense. Hitmontop travel faster
spinning than they do walking.\x
natdex_data0237_hitmontop.name: Hitmontop

natdex_data0238_smoochum.description:
It actively runs about, but also falls
often. Whenever it falls, it will check its
reflection on a lake's surface to make
sure its face hasn't become dirty.\x
natdex_data0238_smoochum.name: Smoochum

natdex_data0239_elekid.description:
If it touches metal and discharges the
electricity it has stored in its body, an
Elekid begins swinging its arms in circles
to recharge itself.\x
natdex_data0239_elekid.name: Elekid

natdex_data0240_magby.description:
If a Magby is spouting yellow flames from
its mouth, it is in good health. When it is
fatigued, black smoke will be mixed in with
the flames.\x
natdex_data0240_magby.name: Magby

natdex_data0241_miltank.description:
It gives over five gallons of milk daily.
Its sweet milk is enjoyed by children and
grown-ups alike. People who can't drink
milk turn it into yogurt and eat it instead.\x
natdex_data0241_miltank.name: Miltank

natdex_data0242_blissey.description:
If it senses sadness with its fluffy fur,
a Blissey will rush over to the sad person,
however far away, to share an egg of
happiness that brings a smile to any face.\x
natdex_data0242_blissey.name: Blissey

natdex_data0243_raikou.description:
Raikou embodies the speed of lightning.
Its roars send shock waves shuddering
through the air and ground as if
lightning bolts were crashing down.\x
natdex_data0243_raikou.name: Raikou

natdex_data0244_entei.description:
Entei embodies the passion of magma.
It is thought to have been born in the
eruption of a volcano. It blasts fire that
consumes all that it touches.\x
natdex_data0244_entei.name: Entei

natdex_data0245_suicune.description:
Suicune embodies the compassion of
a pure spring of water. It runs across
the land with gliding elegance. It has the
power to purify dirty water.\x
natdex_data0245_suicune.name: Suicune

natdex_data0246_larvitar.description:
A Larvitar is born deep under the ground.
It must eat its way through the soil above
and reach the surface for it to see its
parents' faces.\x
natdex_data0246_larvitar.name: Larvitar

natdex_data0247_pupitar.description:
A Pupitar creates a gas inside its body
that it ejects under compression to propel
itself like a jet. Its body can withstand
a collision with solid steel.\x
natdex_data0247_pupitar.name: Pupitar

natdex_data0248_tyranitar.description:
A Tyranitar is so overwhelmingly powerful,
it can bring down a whole mountain to make
its nest. It roams in mountains seeking
new opponents to fight.\x
natdex_data0248_tyranitar.name: Tyranitar

natdex_data0249_lugia.description:
Lugia is so powerful even a light
fluttering of its wings can blow apart
houses. As a result, it chooses to live out
of sight deep under the sea.\x
natdex_data0249_lugia.name: Lugia

natdex_data0250_hooh.description:
Its feathers--which glow in seven colors
depending on the angle at which they are
struck by light--are thought to bring joy.
It is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.\x
natdex_data0250_hooh.name: Ho-oh

natdex_data0251_celebi.description:
This Pokémon came from the future by
crossing over time. It is thought that so
long as Celebi appears, a bright and
shining future awaits us.\x
natdex_data0251_celebi.name: Celebi

natdex_data0252_treecko.description:
It makes its nest in a giant tree in the
forest. It ferociously guards against
anything nearing its territory. It is said
to be the protector of the forest's trees.\x
natdex_data0252_treecko.name: Treecko

natdex_data0253_grovyle.description:
Leaves grow out of this Pokémon's body.
They help obscure a Grovyle from the eyes
of its enemies while it is in a thickly
overgrown forest.\x
natdex_data0253_grovyle.name: Grovyle

natdex_data0254_sceptile.description:
In the jungle, its power is without equal.
This Pokémon carefully grows trees and
plants. It regulates its body temperature
by basking in sunlight.\x
natdex_data0254_sceptile.name: Sceptile

natdex_data0255_torchic.description:
If attacked, it strikes back by spitting
balls of fire it forms in its stomach.
A Torchic dislikes darkness because it
can't see its surroundings.\x
natdex_data0255_torchic.name: Torchic

natdex_data0256_combusken.description:
It lashes out with 10 kicks per second.
Its strong fighting instinct compels it
to keep up its offensive until the
opponent gives up.\x
natdex_data0256_combusken.name: Combusken

natdex_data0257_blaziken.description:
It learns martial arts that use punches
and kicks. Every several years, its old
feathers burn off, and new, supple
feathers grow back in their place.\x
natdex_data0257_blaziken.name: Blaziken

natdex_data0258_mudkip.description:
On land, it can powerfully lift large
boulders by planting its four feet and
heaving. It sleeps by burying itself in soil
at the water's edge.\x
natdex_data0258_mudkip.name: Mudkip

natdex_data0259_marshtomp.description:
Its toughened hind legs enable it to stand
upright. Because it weakens if its skin
dries out, it replenishes fluids by playing
in mud.\x
natdex_data0259_marshtomp.name: Marshtomp

natdex_data0260_swampert.description:
If it senses the approach of a storm and
a tidal wave, it protects its seaside nest
by piling up boulders. It swims as fast as
a jet ski.\x
natdex_data0260_swampert.name: Swampert

natdex_data0261_poochyena.description:
It savagely threatens foes with bared
fangs. It chases after fleeing targets
tenaciously. It turns tail and runs,
however, if the foe strikes back.\x
natdex_data0261_poochyena.name: Poochyena

natdex_data0262_mightyena.description:
In the wild, Mightyena live in a pack.
They never defy their leader's orders.
They defeat foes with perfectly
coordinated teamwork.\x
natdex_data0262_mightyena.name: Mightyena

natdex_data0263_zigzagoon.description:
Rubbing its nose against the ground, it
always wanders about back and forth in
search of something. It is distinguished
by the zigzag footprints it leaves.\x
natdex_data0263_zigzagoon.name: Zigzagoon

natdex_data0264_linoone.description:
It is exceedingly fast if it only has to run
in a straight line. When it spots pond-
dwelling prey underwater, it quickly leaps
in and catches it with its sharp claws.\x
natdex_data0264_linoone.name: Linoone

natdex_data0265_wurmple.description:
It sticks to tree branches and eats
leaves. The thread it spits from its mouth,
which becomes gooey when it touches
air, slows the movement of its foes.\x
natdex_data0265_wurmple.name: Wurmple

natdex_data0266_silcoon.description:
It prepares for evolution using the
energy it stored while it was a Wurmple.
It keeps watch over the surroundings with
its two eyes.\x
natdex_data0266_silcoon.name: Silcoon

natdex_data0267_beautifly.description:
Its colorfully patterned wings are its
most prominent feature. It flies through
flower-covered fields collecting pollen.
It attacks ferociously when angered.\x
natdex_data0267_beautifly.name: Beautifly

natdex_data0268_cascoon.description:
To avoid detection by its enemies, it hides
motionlessly beneath large leaves and in
the gaps of branches. It also attaches
dead leaves to its body for camouflage.\x
natdex_data0268_cascoon.name: Cascoon

natdex_data0269_dustox.description:
It is a nocturnal Pokémon that flies from
fields and mountains to the attraction of
streetlights at night. It looses highly
toxic powder from its wings.\x
natdex_data0269_dustox.name: Dustox

natdex_data0270_lotad.description:
This Pokémon lives in ponds with clean
water. It is known to ferry small Pokémon
across ponds by carrying them on the
broad leaf on its head.\x
natdex_data0270_lotad.name: Lotad

natdex_data0271_lombre.description:
In the evening, it takes great delight in
popping out of rivers and startling people.
It feeds on aquatic moss that grows on
rocks in the riverbed.\x
natdex_data0271_lombre.name: Lombre

natdex_data0272_ludicolo.description:
When it hears festive music, all the cells
in its body become stimulated, and it
begins moving in rhythm. It does not
quail even when it faces a tough opponent.\x
natdex_data0272_ludicolo.name: Ludicolo

natdex_data0273_seedot.description:
It hangs off branches and absorbs
nutrients. When it finishes eating, its
body becomes so heavy that it drops to
the ground with a thump.\x
natdex_data0273_seedot.name: Seedot

natdex_data0274_nuzleaf.description:
A forest-dwelling Pokémon that is skilled
at climbing trees. Its long and pointed
nose is its weak point. It loses power if
the nose is gripped.\x
natdex_data0274_nuzleaf.name: Nuzleaf

natdex_data0275_shiftry.description:
It is said to arrive on chilly, wintry winds.
Feared from long ago as the guardian of
forests, this Pokémon lives in a deep
forest where people do not venture.\x
natdex_data0275_shiftry.name: Shiftry

natdex_data0276_taillow.description:
Although it is small, it is very courageous.
It will take on a larger Skarmory on an
equal footing. However, its will weakens if
it becomes hungry.\x
natdex_data0276_taillow.name: Taillow

natdex_data0277_swellow.description:
A Swellow dives upon prey from far above.
It never misses its targets. It takes to
the skies in search of lands with a warm
climate.\x
natdex_data0277_swellow.name: Swellow

natdex_data0278_wingull.description:
It makes its nest on a sheer cliff at the
edge of the sea. It has trouble keeping
its wings flapping in flight. Instead, it
soars on updrafts.\x
natdex_data0278_wingull.name: Wingull

natdex_data0279_pelipper.description:
It skims the tops of waves as it flies.
When it spots prey, it uses its large beak
to scoop up the victim with water.
It protects its eggs in its beak.\x
natdex_data0279_pelipper.name: Pelipper

natdex_data0280_ralts.description:
A Ralts has the power to sense the
emotions of people and Pokémon with the
horns on its head. It takes cover if it
senses any hostility.\x
natdex_data0280_ralts.name: Ralts

natdex_data0281_kirlia.description:
A Kirlia has the psychic power to create 
a rip in the dimensions and see into the
future. It is said to dance with pleasure
on sunny mornings.\x
natdex_data0281_kirlia.name: Kirlia

natdex_data0282_gardevoir.description:
It apparently does not feel the pull of
gravity because it supports itself with
psychic power. It will give its life to
protect its Trainer.\x
natdex_data0282_gardevoir.name: Gardevoir

natdex_data0283_surskit.description:
They gather on puddles after evening
downpours, gliding across the surface
of water as if sliding. It secretes honey
with a sweet aroma from its head.\x
natdex_data0283_surskit.name: Surskit

natdex_data0284_masquerain.description:
It intimidates foes with the large eyelike
patterns on its antennae. Because it can't
fly if its wings get wet, it shelters itself
from rain under large trees and eaves.\x
natdex_data0284_masquerain.name: Masquerain

natdex_data0285_shroomish.description:
It loves to eat damp, composted soil in
forests. If you enter a forest after a
long rain, you can see many Shroomish
feasting on composted soil.\x
natdex_data0285_shroomish.name: Shroomish

natdex_data0286_breloom.description:
It scatters spores from holes in the cap
on its head. It loves warm and humid
climates. It feeds on trees and plants in
fields and forests.\x
natdex_data0286_breloom.name: Breloom

natdex_data0287_slakoth.description:
It sleeps virtually all day and night long.
It doesn't change its nest its entire life,
but it sometimes travels great distances
by swimming in rivers.\x
natdex_data0287_slakoth.name: Slakoth

natdex_data0288_vigoroth.description:
It can't keep still because its blood boils
with energy. It runs through the fields
and mountains all day to calm itself. If it
doesn't, it can't sleep at night.\x
natdex_data0288_vigoroth.name: Vigoroth

natdex_data0289_slaking.description:
Hordes of Slaking gather around trees
when fruits come into season. They wait
around patiently for ripened fruits to fall
out of the trees.\x
natdex_data0289_slaking.name: Slaking

natdex_data0290_nincada.description:
It makes its nest at the roots of a mighty
tree. Using its whiskerlike antennae, it
probes its surroundings in the
pitch-black darkness of soil.\x
natdex_data0290_nincada.name: Nincada

natdex_data0291_ninjask.description:
Because it darts about vigorously at high
speed, it is very difficult to see. Hearing
its distinctive cries for too long induces
a headache.\x
natdex_data0291_ninjask.name: Ninjask

natdex_data0292_shedinja.description:
A peculiar Pokémon that floats in air even
though its wings remain completely still.
The inside of its body is hollow and
utterly dark.\x
natdex_data0292_shedinja.name: Shedinja

natdex_data0293_whismur.description:
Its cries equal a jet plane in volume.
It inhales through its ear canals. Because
of this system, it can cry continually
without having to catch its breath.\x
natdex_data0293_whismur.name: Whismur

natdex_data0294_loudred.description:
It positions the round speakers on its
head to assail foes with ultrasonic waves
at massive volume. It builds power by
stomping the ground.\x
natdex_data0294_loudred.name: Loudred

natdex_data0295_exploud.description:
It has sound-generating organs all over
its body. It communicates with others by
adjusting the tone and volume of the cries
it emits.\x
natdex_data0295_exploud.name: Exploud

natdex_data0296_makuhita.description:
It loves to toughen up its body above all
else. If you hear quaking rumbles in a cave,
it is the sound of Makuhita undertaking
strenuous training.\x
natdex_data0296_makuhita.name: Makuhita

natdex_data0297_hariyama.description:
It has the habit of challenging others
without hesitation to tests of strength.
It's been known to stand on train tracks
and stop trains using forearm thrusts.\x
natdex_data0297_hariyama.name: Hariyama

natdex_data0298_azurill.description:
Its tail, which is packed with nutrition,
is very bouncy like a rubber ball. On sunny
days they gather at the edge of water and
splash about for fun.\x
natdex_data0298_azurill.name: Azurill

natdex_data0299_nosepass.description:
Its body emits a powerful magnetism.
It feeds on prey that is pulled in by the
force. Its magnetism is stronger in cold
seasons.\x
natdex_data0299_nosepass.name: Nosepass

natdex_data0300_skitty.description:
A Skitty's adorably cute behavior makes it
highly popular. In battle, it makes its tail
puff out. It threatens foes with a sharp
growl.\x
natdex_data0300_skitty.name: Skitty

natdex_data0301_delcatty.description:
Rather than keeping a permanent lair,
it habitually seeks comfortable spots and
sleeps there. It is nocturnal and becomes
active at dusk.\x
natdex_data0301_delcatty.name: Delcatty

natdex_data0302_sableye.description:
It digs branching holes in caves using its
sharp claws in search of food--raw gems.
A Sableye lurks in darkness and is seen
only rarely.\x
natdex_data0302_sableye.name: Sableye

natdex_data0303_mawile.description:
Its giant jaws are actually steel horns
that transformed. It fools foes into
complacency with its adorable gestures,
then chomps them with its huge jaws.\x
natdex_data0303_mawile.name: Mawile

natdex_data0304_aron.description:
A Pokémon that is clad in steel armor.
A new suit of armor is made when it evolves.
The old, discarded armor is salvaged as
metal for making iron products.\x
natdex_data0304_aron.name: Aron

natdex_data0305_lairon.description:
When two Lairon meet in the wild, they
fight for territory by bashing into each
other with their steel bodies. The sound
of their collision carries for miles.\x
natdex_data0305_lairon.name: Lairon

natdex_data0306_aggron.description:
Its iron horns grow longer a little at
a time. They are used to determine the
Aggron's age. The gouges in its armor are
worn with pride as mementos from battles.\x
natdex_data0306_aggron.name: Aggron

natdex_data0307_meditite.description:
It continually meditates for hours every
day. As a result of rigorous and dedicated
yoga training, it has tempered its
spiritual power so much it can fly.\x
natdex_data0307_meditite.name: Meditite

natdex_data0308_medicham.description:
Through crushingly harsh yoga training, it
gained the power to foretell its foe's
actions. It battles with elegant, dance-
like movement.\x
natdex_data0308_medicham.name: Medicham

natdex_data0309_electrike.description:
It generates electricity using friction
from the atmosphere. In seasons with
especially arid air, its entire body blazes
with violent showers of sparks.\x
natdex_data0309_electrike.name: Electrike

natdex_data0310_manectric.description:
Because lightning falls in their vicinities,
Manectric were thought to have been born
from lightning. In battle, they create
thunderclouds.\x
natdex_data0310_manectric.name: Manectric

natdex_data0311_plusle.description:
It has the trait of cheering on its fellow
Pokémon. By shorting out the electricity
it releases from its paws, it creates
pom-poms for cheering.\x
natdex_data0311_plusle.name: Plusle

natdex_data0312_minun.description:
At a meeting of Pokémon academics, it was
announced that simultaneous exposure to
electricity from a Plusle and Minun will
promote circulation and boost vitality.\x
natdex_data0312_minun.name: Minun

natdex_data0313_volbeat.description:
With their taillights lit, Volbeat fly in
a swarm, drawing geometric designs in the
night sky. They move their nests if their
pond water becomes dirty.\x
natdex_data0313_volbeat.name: Volbeat

natdex_data0314_illumise.description:
A nocturnal Pokémon that becomes active
upon nightfall. It leads a Volbeat swarm
to draw patterns in the night sky. Over 200
different patterns have been confirmed.\x
natdex_data0314_illumise.name: Illumise

natdex_data0315_roselia.description:
A Roselia that drinks nutritionally rich
springwater blooms with lovely flowers.
The fragrance of its flowers has the
effect of making its foes careless.\x
natdex_data0315_roselia.name: Roselia

natdex_data0316_gulpin.description:
This Pokémon's stomach fluid can even
digest scrap iron. In one gulp, it can
swallow something that is as large as
itself.\x
natdex_data0316_gulpin.name: Gulpin

natdex_data0317_swalot.description:
Its powerful stomach acid is capable of
digesting almost anything. The one thing
in the whole world a Swalot can't digest is
its own stomach.\x
natdex_data0317_swalot.name: Swalot

natdex_data0318_carvanha.description:
Carvanha attack ships in swarms, making
them sink. Although it is said to be a very
vicious Pokémon, it timidly flees as soon
as it finds itself alone.\x
natdex_data0318_carvanha.name: Carvanha

natdex_data0319_sharpedo.description:
The vicious and sly gangster of the sea.
Its skin is specially textured to minimize
drag in water. Its speed tops out at over
75 miles per hour.\x
natdex_data0319_sharpedo.name: Sharpedo

natdex_data0320_wailmer.description:
While this Pokémon usually lives in the sea,
it can survive on land, although not too
long. It loses vitality if its body becomes
dried out.\x
natdex_data0320_wailmer.name: Wailmer

natdex_data0321_wailord.description:
It breathes through nostrils that it
raises above the sea. By inhaling to its
maximum capacity, a Wailord can dive close
to 10,000 feet beneath the waves.\x
natdex_data0321_wailord.name: Wailord

natdex_data0322_numel.description:
A Numel stores boiling magma in the hump
on its back. It is a hardy Pokémon that can
transport a 220-pound load. It has served
humans at work since long ago.\x
natdex_data0322_numel.name: Numel

natdex_data0323_camerupt.description:
A Pokémon that lives in the crater of
a volcano. Every 10 years, the volcanoes
on its back erupt violently. Research is
under way on the cause of eruption.\x
natdex_data0323_camerupt.name: Camerupt

natdex_data0324_torkoal.description:
It battles using energy it gets from
burning coal. When loosing smoke from its
nostrils, it lets off a sound that is
similar to a locomotive's horn.\x
natdex_data0324_torkoal.name: Torkoal

natdex_data0325_spoink.description:
A Pokémon that manipulates psychic power
at will. It doesn't stop bouncing even when
it is asleep. It loves eating mushrooms
that grow underground.\x
natdex_data0325_spoink.name: Spoink

natdex_data0326_grumpig.description:
It stores power in the black pearls on its
forehead. When it uses psychic power, it
performs an odd dance step. Its style of
dancing became hugely popular overseas.\x
natdex_data0326_grumpig.name: Grumpig

natdex_data0327_spinda.description:
It is distinguished by a pattern of
spots that is always different. Its
unsteady, tottering walk has the
effect of fouling its foe's aim.\x
natdex_data0327_spinda.name: Spinda

natdex_data0328_trapinch.description:
Its big jaws crunch through boulders.
Because its head is so big, it has a hard
time getting back upright if it tips over
onto its back.\x
natdex_data0328_trapinch.name: Trapinch

natdex_data0329_vibrava.description:
It looses ultrasonic waves by rubbing its
wings together. Since a Vibrava's wings
are still in the process of growing, it can
only fly short distances.\x
natdex_data0329_vibrava.name: Vibrava

natdex_data0330_flygon.description:
The flapping of its wings sounds like
singing. To prevent detection by enemies,
it hides itself by flapping up a cloud of
desert sand.\x
natdex_data0330_flygon.name: Flygon

natdex_data0331_cacnea.description:
Cacnea live in deserts with virtually no
rainfall. It battles by swinging its thick,
spiked arms. Once a year, a yellow flower
blooms.\x
natdex_data0331_cacnea.name: Cacnea

natdex_data0332_cacturne.description:
After spending thousands of years in
harsh deserts, its blood transformed into
the same substances as sand. It is
nocturnal, so it hunts at night.\x
natdex_data0332_cacturne.name: Cacturne

natdex_data0333_swablu.description:
A Pokémon that has wings like cottony
clouds. After enduring winter, in which
little food is available, Swablu flocks
move closer to towns in the spring.\x
natdex_data0333_swablu.name: Swablu

natdex_data0334_altaria.description:
It hums in a beautiful soprano voice.
It flies among white clouds in the blue
sky. It launches intensely hot fireballs
from its mouth.\x
natdex_data0334_altaria.name: Altaria

natdex_data0335_zangoose.description:
When it battles, it stands on its hind legs
and attacks with its sharply clawed
forelegs. Its fur bristles if it encounters
any Seviper.\x
natdex_data0335_zangoose.name: Zangoose

natdex_data0336_seviper.description:
Seviper and Zangoose are eternal rivals.
It counters a Zangoose's dazzling agility
with its swordlike tail, which also oozes
a horrible poison.\x
natdex_data0336_seviper.name: Seviper

natdex_data0337_lunatone.description:
It becomes very active on the night of
a full moon. This Pokémon was first
discovered 40 years ago at the site of
a meteor strike.\x
natdex_data0337_lunatone.name: Lunatone

natdex_data0338_solrock.description:
Solar energy is the source of this 
Pokémon's power. On sunny days, groups of
Solrock line up facing the sun and absorb
its light.\x
natdex_data0338_solrock.name: Solrock

natdex_data0339_barboach.description:
Its body is covered with a slimy film.
The film acts as a barrier to prevent germs
in muddy water from entering the
Barboach's body.\x
natdex_data0339_barboach.name: Barboach

natdex_data0340_whiscash.description:
Mysteriously, it can foretell earthquakes.
In the daytime, it sleeps in mud at the
bottom of a pond. When it awakens, it
continually feeds throughout the night.\x
natdex_data0340_whiscash.name: Whiscash

natdex_data0341_corphish.description:
Once it grips prey with its large pincers,
it will never let go, no matter what.
It is a hardy Pokémon that can thrive
in any environment.\x
natdex_data0341_corphish.name: Corphish

natdex_data0342_crawdaunt.description:
A brutish Pokémon that loves to battle.
A veteran Crawdaunt that has prevailed in
hundreds of battles has giant pincers
marked with countless scars.\x
natdex_data0342_crawdaunt.name: Crawdaunt

natdex_data0343_baltoy.description:
A Baltoy moves by spinning on its single
foot. It has been depicted in murals 
adorning the walls of a once-bustling city
in an ancient age.\x
natdex_data0343_baltoy.name: Baltoy

natdex_data0344_claydol.description:
A Claydol sleeps while hovering in midair.
Its arms are separate from its body.
They are kept floating by the Pokémon's
manipulation of psychic power.\x
natdex_data0344_claydol.name: Claydol

natdex_data0345_lileep.description:
It disguises itself as seaweed by making
its tentacles sway. Unsuspecting prey
that come too close are swallowed whole.
It became extinct 100 million years ago.\x
natdex_data0345_lileep.name: Lileep

natdex_data0346_cradily.description:
It drags its heavy body along the
seafloor. It makes its nest in the shallows
of warm seas. Cradily can be seen on
beaches when the tide goes out.\x
natdex_data0346_cradily.name: Cradily

natdex_data0347_anorith.description:
It was resurrected from a fossil using the
power of science. It swims by undulating
the eight wings at its sides. They were
feet that adapted to life in the sea.\x
natdex_data0347_anorith.name: Anorith

natdex_data0348_armaldo.description:
Armaldo usually lives on land. However,
when it hunts for prey, it dives beneath
the ocean. It swims around using its two
large wings.\x
natdex_data0348_armaldo.name: Armaldo

natdex_data0349_feebas.description:
Feebas live in ponds that are heavily
infested with weeds. Because of its
hopelessly shabby appearance, it
seems as if few Trainers raise it.\x
natdex_data0349_feebas.name: Feebas

natdex_data0350_milotic.description:
It is said to live at the bottom of
large lakes. Considered to be the most
beautiful of all Pokémon, it has been
depicted in paintings and statues.\x
natdex_data0350_milotic.name: Milotic

natdex_data0351_castform.description:
It alters its form depending on the
weather. Changes in the climate such as
the temperature and humidity appear to
affect its cellular structure.\x
natdex_data0351_castform.name: Castform

natdex_data0352_kecleon.description:
A Pokémon that has the ability to alter its
body colors to match its surroundings.
A Kecleon reverts to its original colors if
it is startled.\x
natdex_data0352_kecleon.name: Kecleon

natdex_data0353_shuppet.description:
This Pokémon roams about deep in the
night seeking such negative emotions as
grudges and envy. It retreats to its nest
when the sun begins to rise.\x
natdex_data0353_shuppet.name: Shuppet

natdex_data0354_banette.description:
An abandoned plush doll became this
Pokémon. They are said to live in garbage
dumps and wander about in search of the
children that threw them away.\x
natdex_data0354_banette.name: Banette

natdex_data0355_duskull.description:
A glare from its single scarlet eye makes
even burly grown-ups freeze in utter fear.
It is a nocturnal Pokémon that roams
about under the cloak of darkness.\x
natdex_data0355_duskull.name: Duskull

natdex_data0356_dusclops.description:
It is thought that its body is hollow with
only a spectral ball of fire burning inside.
However, no one has been able to
confirm this theory as fact.\x
natdex_data0356_dusclops.name: Dusclops

natdex_data0357_tropius.description:
It flies by flapping its broad leaves.
The bunch of fruit that grows around its
neck is deliciously sweet. In the spring,
it scatters pollen from its neck.\x
natdex_data0357_tropius.name: Tropius

natdex_data0358_chimecho.description:
They fly about very actively when the hot
season arrives. They communicate among
themselves using seven different and
distinguishing cries.\x
natdex_data0358_chimecho.name: Chimecho

natdex_data0359_absol.description:
It sharply senses even subtle changes in
the sky and the land to predict natural
disasters. It is a long-lived Pokémon that
has a life-span of 100 years.\x
natdex_data0359_absol.name: Absol

natdex_data0360_wynaut.description:
A Wynaut loves to eat sweet fruits.
It cleverly picks fruits using its earlike
arms. They gather in fruit gardens, drawn
by the fragrance.\x
natdex_data0360_wynaut.name: Wynaut

natdex_data0361_snorunt.description:
They tend to move about in groups of
around five Snorunt. In snowy regions,
it is said that when they are seen late at
night, snowfall will arrive by morning.\x
natdex_data0361_snorunt.name: Snorunt

natdex_data0362_glalie.description:
A Glalie has the power to instantaneously
freeze moisture in the atmosphere.
A dazzling cloud of diamondlike ice
crystals forms around its body.\x
natdex_data0362_glalie.name: Glalie

natdex_data0363_spheal.description:
It is completely covered with plushy fur.
As a result, it never feels the cold even
when it is rolling about on ice floes or
diving in the sea.\x
natdex_data0363_spheal.name: Spheal

natdex_data0364_sealeo.description:
Sealeo live in herds on ice floes. Using its
powerful flippers, it shatters ice.
It dives into the sea to hunt prey five
times a day.\x
natdex_data0364_sealeo.name: Sealeo

natdex_data0365_walrein.description:
To protect its herd, the leader battles
anything that invades its territory, even
at the cost of its life. Its tusks may snap
off in battle.\x
natdex_data0365_walrein.name: Walrein

natdex_data0366_clamperl.description:
A Clamperl slams its shell closed on prey
to prevent escape. The pearl it creates
upon evolution is said to be infused with
a mysterious energy.\x
natdex_data0366_clamperl.name: Clamperl

natdex_data0367_huntail.description:
To withstand the crushing pressure of
water deep under the sea, its spine is very
thick and sturdy. Its tail, which is shaped
like a small fish, has eyes that light up.\x
natdex_data0367_huntail.name: Huntail

natdex_data0368_gorebyss.description:
A Gorebyss siphons the body fluids of prey
through its thin, tubular mouth. Its light
pink body color turns vivid when it
finishes feeding.\x
natdex_data0368_gorebyss.name: Gorebyss
