natdex_data0369_relicanth.description:
A Pokémon that was once believed to have
been extinct. The species has not changed
its form for 100 million years. It walks on
the seafloor using its pectoral fins.\x
natdex_data0369_relicanth.name: Relicanth

natdex_data0370_luvdisc.description:
Luvdisc make the branches of Corsola
their nests. There is a custom from long
ago of giving a Luvdisc as a gift to
express one's feelings of love.\x
natdex_data0370_luvdisc.name: Luvdisc

natdex_data0371_bagon.description:
Although it is small, this Pokémon is very
powerful because its body is a bundle of
muscles. It launches head-butts with its
ironlike skull.\x
natdex_data0371_bagon.name: Bagon

natdex_data0372_shelgon.description:
It hardly eats while it awaits evolution.
It becomes hardier by enduring hunger.
Its shell peels off the instant it begins
to evolve.\x
natdex_data0372_shelgon.name: Shelgon

natdex_data0373_salamence.description:
After many long years, its cellular
structure underwent a sudden mutation to
grow wings. When angered, it loses all
thought and rampages out of control.\x
natdex_data0373_salamence.name: Salamence

natdex_data0374_beldum.description:
When Beldum gather in a swarm, they move
in perfect unison as if they were but one
Pokémon. They communicate with each other
using brain waves.\x
natdex_data0374_beldum.name: Beldum

natdex_data0375_metang.description:
The claws tipping its arms pack the
destructive power to tear through thick
iron sheets as if they were silk. It flies
at over 60 miles per hour.\x
natdex_data0375_metang.name: Metang

natdex_data0376_metagross.description:
Metagross has four brains that are joined
by a complex neural network. As a result of
integration, this Pokémon is smarter than
a supercomputer.\x
natdex_data0376_metagross.name: Metagross

natdex_data0377_regirock.description:
A Pokémon that is made entirely of rocks
and boulders. If parts of its body chip off
in battle, Regirock repairs itself by
adding new rocks.\x
natdex_data0377_regirock.name: Regirock

natdex_data0378_regice.description:
Its entire body is made of Antarctic ice.
After extensive studies, researchers
believe the ice was formed during an
ice age.\x
natdex_data0378_regice.name: Regice

natdex_data0379_registeel.description:
Its body is harder than any other kind of
metal. The body metal is composed of a
mysterious substance. Not only is it hard,
it shrinks and stretches flexibly.\x
natdex_data0379_registeel.name: Registeel

natdex_data0380_latias.description:
They make a small herd of only several
members. They rarely make contact with
people or other Pokémon. They disappear
if they sense enemies.\x
natdex_data0380_latias.name: Latias

natdex_data0381_latios.description:
Even in hiding, it can detect the locations
of others and sense their emotions since
it has telepathy. Its intelligence allows
it to understand human languages.\x
natdex_data0381_latios.name: Latios

natdex_data0382_kyogre.description:
Kyogre has appeared in mythology as the
creator of the sea. After long years of
feuding with Groudon, it took to sleep at
the bottom of the sea.\x
natdex_data0382_kyogre.name: Kyogre

natdex_data0383_groudon.description:
Groudon has appeared in mythology as the
creator of the land. It sleeps in magma
underground and is said to make volcanoes
erupt on awakening.\x
natdex_data0383_groudon.name: Groudon

natdex_data0384_rayquaza.description:
A Pokémon that flies endlessly in the
ozone layer. It is said it would descend
to the ground if Kyogre and Groudon
were to fight.\x
natdex_data0384_rayquaza.name: Rayquaza

natdex_data0385_jirachi.description:
Jirachi is said to make wishes come true.
While it sleeps, a tough crystalline shell
envelops the body to protect it from
enemies.\x
natdex_data0385_jirachi.name: Jirachi

natdex_data0386_deoxys.description:
Deoxys emerged from a virus that came
from space. It is highly intelligent and
can shoot lasers from the crystalline
organ on its chest.\x
natdex_data0386_deoxys.name: Deoxys

natdex_data0387_turtwig.description:
The shell on its back is made of soil. 
On a very healthy Turtwig, the shell 
should feel moist. The leaf on its head
wilts if it is thirsty.\x
natdex_data0387_turtwig.name: Turtwig

natdex_data0388_grotle.description:
A Grotle that lives in the forest is said
to have its own secret springwater well. 
It carries fellow Pokémon there on 
its back.\x
natdex_data0388_grotle.name: Grotle

natdex_data0389_torterra.description:
Some Pokémon are born on a Torterra's
back and spend their entire life there.
Ancient people imagined that beneath 
the ground, a gigantic Torterra dwelled.\x
natdex_data0389_torterra.name: Torterra

natdex_data0390_chimchar.description:
Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made
in its belly. Before going to sleep,
Chimchar extinguish the flame on their
tails to prevent fires.\x
natdex_data0390_chimchar.name: Chimchar

natdex_data0391_monferno.description:
It carefully controls the intensity of
the flame on its tail, so as to keep its
foes at an adequate distance.
Its fiery tail is but one weapon.\x
natdex_data0391_monferno.name: Monferno

natdex_data0392_infernape.description:
Its crown of fire is indicative of its
fiery nature. It uses a special kind of
martial arts involving all of its limbs to
take on any opponent.\x
natdex_data0392_infernape.name: Infernape

natdex_data0393_piplup.description:
A poor walker, it often falls down. However,
its strong pride makes it puff up its chest
without a care. It's difficult to bond with
since it won't listen to its Trainer.\x
natdex_data0393_piplup.name: Piplup

natdex_data0394_prinplup.description:
Because every Prinplup considers itself
to be the most important, they can never
form a group. It searches for prey in
icy seas.\x
natdex_data0394_prinplup.name: Prinplup

natdex_data0395_empoleon.description:
The three horns that extend from its beak
attest to its power. It avoids unnecessary
disputes, but it will decimate anything
that threatens its pride.\x
natdex_data0395_empoleon.name: Empoleon

natdex_data0396_starly.description:
They flock around mountains and fields,
chasing after bug Pokémon. However,
they bicker if the group grows too big.
Their singing is noisy and annoying.\x
natdex_data0396_starly.name: Starly

natdex_data0397_staravia.description:
Recognizing their own weakness, they
maintain huge flocks. Fierce scuffles
break out between various flocks.
When alone, a Staravia cries noisily.\x
natdex_data0397_staravia.name: Staravia

natdex_data0398_staraptor.description:
When Staravia evolve into Staraptor,
they leave the flock to live alone. It has
a savage nature. It will courageously
challenge foes that are much larger.\x
natdex_data0398_staraptor.name: Staraptor

natdex_data0399_bidoof.description:
A comparison revealed that Bidoof's front
teeth grow at the same rate as Rattata's.
It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to
whittle down its front teeth.\x
natdex_data0399_bidoof.name: Bidoof

natdex_data0400_bibarel.description:
It makes its nest by damming streams
with bark and mud. A river dammed by
Bibarel will never overflow its banks,
which is appreciated by people nearby.\x
natdex_data0400_bibarel.name: Bibarel

natdex_data0401_kricketot.description:
It shakes its head back to front,
causing its antennae to hit each other
and sound like a xylophone.
These sounds are fall hallmarks.\x
natdex_data0401_kricketot.name: Kricketot

natdex_data0402_kricketune.description:
It signals its emotions with its melodies.
There is a village that hosts a contest
based on the amazingly variable cries
of this Pokémon.\x
natdex_data0402_kricketune.name: Kricketune

natdex_data0403_shinx.description:
It rapidly contracts and relaxes its
muscles to generate electricity. Its
body shines if endangered. It flees
while the foe is momentarily blinded.\x
natdex_data0403_shinx.name: Shinx

natdex_data0404_luxio.description:
Strong electricity courses through the
tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch
has enough amperage to cause fainting
in foes.\x
natdex_data0404_luxio.name: Luxio

natdex_data0405_luxray.description:
It has eyes which can see through
anything. Luxray's ability to see
through objects comes in handy when
it's scouting for danger.\x
natdex_data0405_luxray.name: Luxray

natdex_data0406_budew.description:
Over the winter, it closes its bud and
endures the cold. Sensitive to changing
temperature, the bud is said to bloom
when it feels the sun's warm touch.\x
natdex_data0406_budew.name: Budew

natdex_data0407_roserade.description:
Its sweet aroma attracts prey.
With the movements of a dancer,
it strikes with whips that are densely
lined with poison thorns.\x
natdex_data0407_roserade.name: Roserade

natdex_data0408_cranidos.description:
A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million
years ago, its skull is as hard as iron. 
It would snap obstructing trees with
headbutts.\x
natdex_data0408_cranidos.name: Cranidos

natdex_data0409_rampardos.description:
The result of repeated headbutts
is a skull grown thick and hard.
However, its brain has shrunk in size
compared with Cranidos's.\x
natdex_data0409_rampardos.name: Rampardos

natdex_data0410_shieldon.description:
This Pokémon lived in primeval jungles.
Few enemies would have been willing to
square off against its heavily armored
face, so it's thought.\x
natdex_data0410_shieldon.name: Shieldon

natdex_data0411_bastiodon.description:
Their rock-hard faces serve to protect
them from any frontral attacks.
When attacked, they form a wall.
They shielded their young in that way.\x
natdex_data0411_bastiodon.name: Bastiodon

natdex_data0412_burmy.description:
It is covered with a cloak that shelters
it from the cold. If its cloak is broken
in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak
with materials nearby.\x
natdex_data0412_burmy.name: Burmy

natdex_data0413_wormadam.description:
Its appearance changes depending
on where Burmy evolved. The materials
on hand become a part of its body.
The cloak is never shed.\x
natdex_data0413_wormadam.name: Wormadam

natdex_data0414_mothim.description:
It does not keep a nest. While it
loves floral honey, it won't gather
any itself. Instead, it plots to steal
honey collected by Combee.\x
natdex_data0414_mothim.name: Mothim

natdex_data0415_combee.description:
A Pokémon formed by three others.
It constantly gathers honey from flowers
to please Vespiquen. At night, they
cluster to form a beehive and sleep.\x
natdex_data0415_combee.name: Combee

natdex_data0416_vespiquen.description:
It houses its colony in cells in its body
and releases various pheromones to
make those grubs do its bidding.
There is only one in a colony.\x
natdex_data0416_vespiquen.name: Vespiquen

natdex_data0417_pachirisu.description:
A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek
pouches together in an effort to share
stored electricity. It stores them with
berries in tree holes.\x
natdex_data0417_pachirisu.name: Pachirisu

natdex_data0418_buizel.description:
It inflates its flotation sac, keeping its
face above water in order to watch for
prey movement. It swims by rotating its
two tails like a screw.\x
natdex_data0418_buizel.name: Buizel

natdex_data0419_floatzel.description:
Its flotation sac developed as a result
of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double
as a rubber raft. It assists in the rescues
of drowning people.\x
natdex_data0419_floatzel.name: Floatzel

natdex_data0420_cherubi.description:
The small ball holds the nutrients needed
for evolution. Apparently, it is also very
sweet and tasty. Pokémon like Starly and
Taillow try to peck it off.\x
natdex_data0420_cherubi.name: Cherubi

natdex_data0421_cherrim.description:
During times of strong sunlight, its bud
blooms, its petals open fully, and it
becomes very active. It folds back into
a bud if sunlight wanes.\x
natdex_data0421_cherrim.name: Cherrim

natdex_data0422_shellos.description:
Its shape and coloration vary, depending
on its habitat. Beware of pushing strongly
on its squishy body, as it makes a
mysterious purple fluid ooze out.\x
natdex_data0422_shellos.name: Shellos

natdex_data0423_gastrodon.description:
It lives in shallow tidal pools.
Gastrodon once had a huge shell for
protection in ancient times. There are
traces of it left in its cells.\x
natdex_data0423_gastrodon.name: Gastrodon

natdex_data0424_ambipom.description:
They live on large trees. Split into two,
the tails are so adept at handling and
doing things, Ambipom rarely uses
its hands now.
\x
natdex_data0424_ambipom.name: Ambipom

natdex_data0425_drifloon.description:
Because of the way it floats aimlessly,
an old folktale calls it a ["]Signpost for
Wandering Spirits." Children holding
them sometimes vanish.\x
natdex_data0425_drifloon.name: Drifloon

natdex_data0426_drifblim.description:
Even while under careful observation,
large flocks of Drifblim flying at dusk
will inexplicably disappear from view.
No one knows where they go.\x
natdex_data0426_drifblim.name: Drifblim

natdex_data0427_buneary.description:
You can tell how it feels by the way
it rolls its ears. When it's scared,
both ears are rolled up. When it senses
danger, it perks them up.\x
natdex_data0427_buneary.name: Buneary

natdex_data0428_lopunny.description:
An extremely cautious Pokémon.
It is very conscious of its looks and
never fails to groom its ears.
It runs with sprightly jumps.\x
natdex_data0428_lopunny.name: Lopunny

natdex_data0429_mismagius.description:
Its cries sound like incantations.
Those hearing it are tormented by
headaches and hallucinations.
It appears where you least expect it.\x
natdex_data0429_mismagius.name: Mismagius

natdex_data0430_honchkrow.description:
Becoming active at night, it is known
to swarm with numerous Murkrow in tow.
It is said that it never forgives the
mistakes of its cronies.\x
natdex_data0430_honchkrow.name: Honchkrow

natdex_data0431_glameow.description:
It is a very fickle Pokémon, which is 
very popular among some. It claws its
Trainer's nose if it isn't fed and
purrs when affectionate.\x
natdex_data0431_glameow.name: Glameow

natdex_data0432_purugly.description:
It is a brazen brute that barges its way
into another Pokémon's nest and claims
it as its own. It binds its body with its
tails to make itself look bigger.\x
natdex_data0432_purugly.name: Purugly

natdex_data0433_chingling.description:
There is an orb inside its mouth.
When it hops, the orb bounces all
over and makes a ringing sound.
It can cry for an awfully long time.\x
natdex_data0433_chingling.name: Chingling

natdex_data0434_stunky.description:
It protects itself by spraying a
nose-curling, stinky fluid from its rear
to repel attackers. The stench lingers
for 24 hours.\x
natdex_data0434_stunky.name: Stunky

natdex_data0435_skuntank.description:
It attacks by spraying a horribly smelly
fluid from the tip of its tail. The fluid
smells worse the longer it is allowed
to fester.\x
natdex_data0435_skuntank.name: Skuntank

natdex_data0436_bronzor.description:
Implements shaped like it were discovered
in ancient tombs. There are researchers
who believe this Pokémon reflected like a
mirror in the distant past.\x
natdex_data0436_bronzor.name: Bronzor

natdex_data0437_bronzong.description:
In ages past, this Pokémon was revered as
a bringer of rain. One caused a news stir
when it was dug up at a construction site
after a 2000-year sleep.\x
natdex_data0437_bronzong.name: Bronzong

natdex_data0438_bonsly.description:
Bonsly prefers an arid atmosphere.
In order to adjust the level of fluids
in its body, it exudes water from its eyes.
This makes it appear to be crying.\x
natdex_data0438_bonsly.name: Bonsly

natdex_data0439_mimejr.description:
In an attempt to confuse its enemy,
it mimics the enemy's movements.
Once mimicked, the foe cannot take
its eyes off this Pokémon.\x
natdex_data0439_mimejr.name: Mime Jr.

natdex_data0440_happiny.description:
It carries a round white rock in its
belly pouch. If it gets along well with
someone, it will sometimes give that
person the rock.\x
natdex_data0440_happiny.name: Happiny

natdex_data0441_chatot.description:
It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to
trick them into thinking it's one of them.
This way they won't attack it. It can
also learn and speak human words.\x
natdex_data0441_chatot.name: Chatot

natdex_data0442_spiritomb.description:
A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits.
Its constant mischief and misdeeds
resulted in it being bound to an
Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.\x
natdex_data0442_spiritomb.name: Spiritomb

natdex_data0443_gible.description:
It nests in horizontal holes warmed by
geothermal heat. Foes who stray too
close can expect to be pounced on
and bitten.\x
natdex_data0443_gible.name: Gible

natdex_data0444_gabite.description:
Shiny objects are its passion. It can be
found in its cave, scarcely moving,
its gaze fixed on the jewels it's amassed
or Carbink it has caught.\x
natdex_data0444_gabite.name: Gabite

natdex_data0445_garchomp.description:
When it folds up its body and extends its
wings, it looks like a jet plane. It is
covered in fine scales that reduce drag,
enabling it to fly at high speeds.\x
natdex_data0445_garchomp.name: Garchomp

natdex_data0446_munchlax.description:
When it finds something that looks like
it might be edible, it goes right ahead
and swallows it whole. That's why it gets
fatter day by day.\x
natdex_data0446_munchlax.name: Munchlax

natdex_data0447_riolu.description:
It can discern the physical and emotional
states of people, Pokémon, and other
natural things from the shape of their
aura waves.\x
natdex_data0447_riolu.name: Riolu

natdex_data0448_lucario.description:
It understands human speech.
It is said that no foe can remain invisible
to Lucario, since it can detect Auras.
Even foes it could not otherwise see.\x
natdex_data0448_lucario.name: Lucario

natdex_data0449_hippopotas.description:
Hippopotas shuts its nostrils tight when
travelling through sand. Instead of
perspiration, it expels grains of sand
from its body.\x
natdex_data0449_hippopotas.name: Hippopotas

natdex_data0450_hippowdon.description:
It is surprisingly quick to anger.
It brandishes its gaping mouth in a
display of fearsome strength and raises
vast quantities of sand while attacking.\x
natdex_data0450_hippowdon.name: Hippowdon

natdex_data0451_skorupi.description:
It grips prey with its tail claws and
injects poison. It tenaciously hangs
on until the poison takes.
It can survive a year without food.\x
natdex_data0451_skorupi.name: Skorupi

natdex_data0452_drapion.description:
Possessing a sturdy build, it takes
pride in its strength. It has the power
in its clawed arms to make scrap
out of a car.\x
natdex_data0452_drapion.name: Drapion

natdex_data0453_croagunk.description:
Croagunk rarely fights fairly. Inflating
its poison sacs, it fills the area with
an odd sound and hits flinching
opponents with a poison jab.\x
natdex_data0453_croagunk.name: Croagunk

natdex_data0454_toxicroak.description:
Swaying and dodging the attacks
of its foes, it weaves its flexible body
in close, then lunges out with its
poisonous claws.\x
natdex_data0454_toxicroak.name: Toxicroak

natdex_data0455_carnivine.description:
Hanging from branches using its
tentacles, it looks like a plant.
It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling
saliva, then chomps down.\x
natdex_data0455_carnivine.name: Carnivine

natdex_data0456_finneon.description:
Its double tail fins propel its energetic
jumps. When it breaks the surface of the
sea, Wingull swoop down to grab it on
the fly.\x
natdex_data0456_finneon.name: Finneon

natdex_data0457_lumineon.description:
Lumineon swimming in the darkness
of the deep sea look like stars shining
in the night sky. It competes for food
with Lanturn.\x
natdex_data0457_lumineon.name: Lumineon

natdex_data0458_mantyke.description:
When it swims close to the surface
of the ocean, people aboard ships are
able to observe the pattern on its back.
It often swims in a school of Remoraid.\x
natdex_data0458_mantyke.name: Mantyke

natdex_data0459_snover.description:
During cold seasons, it migrates to the
mountain's lower reaches. Seemingly
curious about people, they gather around
footsteps they find on snowy mountains.\x
natdex_data0459_snover.name: Snover

natdex_data0460_abomasnow.description:
It lives a quiet life on mountains that
are perpetually covered in snow. It hides
itself by whipping up blizzards.
It is also known as ["]The Ice Monster."\x
natdex_data0460_abomasnow.name: Abomasnow

natdex_data0461_weavile.description:
They travel in groups of four or five,
leaving signs for one another on trees
and rocks. They bring down their prey
with coordinated attacks.\x
natdex_data0461_weavile.name: Weavile

natdex_data0462_magnezone.description:
As it zooms through the sky, this
Pokémon seems to be receiving signals
of unknown origin, while transmitting its
own signals of unknown purpose.\x
natdex_data0462_magnezone.name: Magnezone

natdex_data0463_lickilicky.description:
The long tongue is always soggy with
slobber. The saliva contains a solvent
that causes numbness. Getting too close
to it will leave you soaked with drool.\x
natdex_data0463_lickilicky.name: Lickilicky

natdex_data0464_rhyperior.description:
It can launch a rock held in its hand
like a missile by tightening and then
expanding its muscles instantaneously.
Geodude are shot at rare times.\x
natdex_data0464_rhyperior.name: Rhyperior

natdex_data0465_tangrowth.description:
It ensnares prey by extending arms made
of vines. Even if one of its arms is eaten,
it's fine. The Pokémon regenerates quickly
and will go right back to normal.\x
natdex_data0465_tangrowth.name: Tangrowth

natdex_data0466_electivire.description:
When it gets excited, it thumps its chest.
With every thud, thunder roars, electric
sparks shower all around and blue sparks
begin to crackle between its horns.\x
natdex_data0466_electivire.name: Electivire

natdex_data0467_magmortar.description:
According to what is known, a single pair
of male and female Magmortar lives in
one volcano. From its arm, it launches
fireballs hotter than 3,600\h2AF.\x
natdex_data0467_magmortar.name: Magmortar

natdex_data0468_togekiss.description:
As everyone knows, it visits peaceful
regions, bringing them gifts of kindness
and sweet blessings. It will never appear
where there is strife.\x
natdex_data0468_togekiss.name: Togekiss

natdex_data0469_yanmega.description:
This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable
of transporting an adult in flight. It is
adept at biting apart foes while flying
by at high speed.\x
natdex_data0469_yanmega.name: Yanmega

natdex_data0470_leafeon.description:
Its cellular composition is closer to
that of a plant than an animal. It uses
photosynthesis to produce its energy
supply without eating food.\x
natdex_data0470_leafeon.name: Leafeon

natdex_data0471_glaceon.description:
It can control its body temperature
at will. This enables it to freeze the
moisture in the atmosphere, creating
flurries of diamond dust.\x
natdex_data0471_glaceon.name: Glaceon

natdex_data0472_gliscor.description:
Gliscor observes prey while hanging
upside down from branches. Its flight is
soundless. When the chance presents
itself, it swoops!\x
natdex_data0472_gliscor.name: Gliscor

natdex_data0473_mamoswine.description:
A frozen Mamoswine was dug from ice
dating back 10,000 years. It woke up to
much amazement. This Pokémon has been
around for a long, long, long time.\x
natdex_data0473_mamoswine.name: Mamoswine

natdex_data0474_porygonz.description:
In order to create a more advanced
Pokémon, an additional program was
installed, but apparently it contained a
defect that made it move oddly.\x
natdex_data0474_porygonz.name: Porygon-Z

natdex_data0475_gallade.description:
A master of courtesy and swordsmanship,
it fights using extending swords on its
elbows when trying to protect someone.
It can sense what its foe is thinking.\x
natdex_data0475_gallade.name: Gallade

natdex_data0476_probopass.description:
It freely controls three units called
Mini-Noses using magnetic force.
With them, it can attack its foes from
three directions.\x
natdex_data0476_probopass.name: Probopass

natdex_data0477_dusknoir.description:
This feared Pokémon is said to travel to
worlds unknown. Some even believe that
it takes lost spirits into its pliant body
and guides them home.\x
natdex_data0477_dusknoir.name: Dusknoir

natdex_data0478_froslass.description:
When it finds people or Pokémon it likes,
it freezes them and takes them to its
chilly den, where they become its
decorations.\x
natdex_data0478_froslass.name: Froslass

natdex_data0479_rotom.description:
Research continues on this Pokémon.
Its electric-like body can enter some
kinds of machines and take control,
in order to make mischief.\x
natdex_data0479_rotom.name: Rotom

natdex_data0480_uxie.description:
Known as "The Being of Knowledge,"
according to some sources, this Pokémon
provided people with the intelligence
necessary to solve various problems.\x
natdex_data0480_uxie.name: Uxie

natdex_data0481_mesprit.description:
Although it slumbers at the bottom of a
lake, its spirit is said to leave its body
and flitter on the water surface. It
taught humans of sorrow, pain, and joy.\x
natdex_data0481_mesprit.name: Mesprit

natdex_data0482_azelf.description:
This Pokémon is said to have endowed
humans with the determination needed to
do things. It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit
and Azelf all came from the same egg.\x
natdex_data0482_azelf.name: Azelf

natdex_data0483_dialga.description:
A Pokémon spoken of in legend.
It completely controls the flow of time.
It uses its power to travel at will
through the past and future.\x
natdex_data0483_dialga.name: Dialga

natdex_data0484_palkia.description:
Palkia has the ability to distort space.
Its total control over the boundaries of
space enable it to transport itself to
faraway places and other dimensions.\x
natdex_data0484_palkia.name: Palkia

natdex_data0485_heatran.description:
Boiling blood, like magma, circulates
through its body. It dwells in volcanic
caves, using its cross-shaped feet
to crawl on ceilings and walls.\x
natdex_data0485_heatran.name: Heatran

natdex_data0486_regigigas.description:
There is an enduring legend that
states this Pokémon shaped Regirock,
Regice, and Registeel out of clay, ice,
and magma.\x
natdex_data0486_regigigas.name: Regigigas

natdex_data0487_giratina.description:
This Pokémon is said to live in a world
on the reverse side of ours, where common
knowledge is distorted and strange.
It was banished for its violence.\x
natdex_data0487_giratina.name: Giratina

natdex_data0488_cresselia.description:
Those who sleep holding one of
Cresselia's feathers are assured of
joyful dreams. It is said to represent
the crescent moon.\x
natdex_data0488_cresselia.name: Cresselia

natdex_data0489_phione.description:
When the water warms, they inflate the
flotation sac on their heads and drift
languidly on the sea in packs.
It always returns to where it was born.\x
natdex_data0489_phione.name: Phione

natdex_data0490_manaphy.description:
Water makes up 80% of its body.
It starts its life with a wondrous power
that permits it to bond with any kind
of Pokémon.\x
natdex_data0490_manaphy.name: Manaphy

natdex_data0491_darkrai.description:
It chases people and Pokémon from its
territory by causing them to experience
deep, nightmarish slumbers. However,
it means no harm.\x
natdex_data0491_darkrai.name: Darkrai

natdex_data0492_shaymin.description:
The flowers all over its body burst into
bloom if it is lovingly hugged and senses
gratitude. The blooming of Gracideas
confers the power of flight upon it.\x
natdex_data0492_shaymin.name: Shaymin

natdex_data0493_arceus.description:
It is told in mythology that this Pokémon
emerged from an egg and shaped all there
is in this world, before the universe
even existed.\x
natdex_data0493_arceus.name: Arceus

natdex_data0494_victini.description:
This Pokémon brings victory.
It is said that Trainers with Victini
always win, regardless of the type
of encounter.\x
natdex_data0494_victini.name: Victini

natdex_data0495_snivy.description:
It is very intelligent and calm.
Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes
its movements swifter. When they are
not feeling well, their tails droop.\x
natdex_data0495_snivy.name: Snivy

natdex_data0496_servine.description:
When it gets dirty, its leaves can't be
used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps
clean. They avoid attacks by sinking into
the shadows of thick foliage.\x
natdex_data0496_servine.name: Servine

natdex_data0497_serperior.description:
They raise their heads to intimidate foes,
but only give it their all when fighting
powerful opponents who are not fazed
by the glare from its noble eyes.\x
natdex_data0497_serperior.name: Serperior

natdex_data0498_tepig.description:
It loves to eat roasted berries, but
sometimes it gets too excited and burns
them to a crisp. It blows fire through
its nose.\x
natdex_data0498_tepig.name: Tepig

natdex_data0499_pignite.description:
The more it eats, the more fuel it has
to make the fire in its stomach stronger.
When it is angered, the intensity of the
flame increases.\x
natdex_data0499_pignite.name: Pignite

natdex_data0500_emboar.description:
It is adept at using many different moves.
It can throw a fire punch by setting its
fists on fire with its fiery chin.
It cares deeply about its friends.\x
natdex_data0500_emboar.name: Emboar

natdex_data0501_oshawott.description:
The scalchop on its stomach isn't just
used for battle, it can be used to break
open hard berries as well. It is made
from the same element as its claws.\x
natdex_data0501_oshawott.name: Oshawott

natdex_data0502_dewott.description:
Strict training and disclipine leads it
to master its flowing double-scalchop
technique. Scalchop techniques differ
from one Dewott to another.\x
natdex_data0502_dewott.name: Dewott

natdex_data0503_samurott.description:
One swing of the seamitars attached
to its armor can fell an opponent.
A simple glare from one of them is
enough to intimidate most enemies.\x
natdex_data0503_samurott.name: Samurott

natdex_data0504_patrat.description:
Extremely cautious, they take shifts to
maintain a constant watch of their nest.
Using food stored in cheek pouches,
they can keep watch for days.\x
natdex_data0504_patrat.name: Patrat

natdex_data0505_watchog.description:
Using luminescent matter, it makes its
eyes and body glow and stuns attacking
opponents. Keen eyesight lets them see
in the dark.\x
natdex_data0505_watchog.name: Watchog

natdex_data0506_lillipup.description:
It faces strong opponents with great
courage. Because it doesn't yelp, it's
extremely popular with Trainers who live
in apartment buildings.\x
natdex_data0506_lillipup.name: Lillipup

natdex_data0507_herdier.description:
Its dense black fur grows continuously.
The high cost of keeping its hard fur
properly groomed makes this a
troublesome Pokémon to train.
\x
natdex_data0507_herdier.name: Herdier

natdex_data0508_stoutland.description:
Intelligent, good-natured, and valiant,
there could be no concern that it would
ever attack people. Some parents even
trust it to babysit.\x
natdex_data0508_stoutland.name: Stoutland

natdex_data0509_purrloin.description:
Their deceptively cute act is the
perfect ruse. They steal from people for
fun, but their victims can't help but
forgive them.\x
natdex_data0509_purrloin.name: Purrloin

natdex_data0510_liepard.description:
Many Trainers are drawn to their
beautiful form and fur. These Pokémon
vanish and appear unexpectedly.
They run silently in the night.\x
natdex_data0510_liepard.name: Liepard

natdex_data0511_pansage.description:
This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest.
It's good at finding berries and gathers
them from all over. It's kind enough to
share them with friends.\x
natdex_data0511_pansage.name: Pansage

natdex_data0512_simisage.description:
Ill tempered, it attacks enemies by
swinging its barbed tail around wildly.
The leaf growing on its head is
very bitter.\x
natdex_data0512_simisage.name: Simisage

natdex_data0513_pansear.description:
The fire within the tuft on its head can
reach up to 600\h2AF. Very intelligent,
it roasts berries before eating them.
It likes to help people.\x
natdex_data0513_pansear.name: Pansear

natdex_data0514_simisear.description:
It loves sweets because they become
energy for the fire burning inside its
body. It scatters embers from its head
and tail to sear its opponents.\x
natdex_data0514_simisear.name: Simisear

natdex_data0515_panpour.description:
The water stored inside the tuft of its
head is rich in nutrients. It waters
plants using its tail, plants that
receive its water grow large.\x
natdex_data0515_panpour.name: Panpour

natdex_data0516_simipour.description:
It can shoot highly-pressurised water
from its tail with enough power to
break through a solid concrete wall.
It prefers places with clean water.\x
natdex_data0516_simipour.name: Simipour

natdex_data0517_munna.description:
This Pokémon appears before people
and Pokémon who are having nightmares
and eats those dreams. Munna always
float in the air. \x
natdex_data0517_munna.name: Munna

natdex_data0518_musharna.description:
The mist emanating from their foreheads
is packed with the dreams of people and
Pokémon. It changes into different colors
depending on the dream that was eaten.\x
natdex_data0518_musharna.name: Musharna

natdex_data0519_pidove.description:
This very forgetful Pokémon will wait for
a new order from its Trainer even though
it already has one. Flocks often gather
in parks and plazas.\x
natdex_data0519_pidove.name: Pidove

natdex_data0520_tranquill.description:
No matter where in the world it goes,
it knows where its nest is, so it can
always return to its Trainer's location
regardless of the distance.\x
natdex_data0520_tranquill.name: Tranquill

natdex_data0521_unfezant.description:
Males have plumage on their heads.
The females' flying abilities surpass
those of the males. They will only let
themselves feel close to their Trainers.\x
natdex_data0521_unfezant.name: Unfezant

natdex_data0522_blitzle.description:
Its mane shines when it discharges
electricity. They use the frequency and
rhythm of these flashes to communicate
with one another.\x
natdex_data0522_blitzle.name: Blitzle

natdex_data0523_zebstrika.description:
When Zebstrika run at full speed, the
sound of thunder reverberates. It is
dangerous when it's angry as it shoots
lightning from its mane in all directions.\x
natdex_data0523_zebstrika.name: Zebstrika

natdex_data0524_roggenrola.description:
The hexagonal cavity is its ear.
It walks in the direction of sounds it
hears, but if the sounds cease, it panics
and topples over.\x
natdex_data0524_roggenrola.name: Roggenrola

natdex_data0525_boldore.description:
Its orange crystal is a mass of energy.
Just one crystal fragment would provide
enough fuel for a hundred dump trucks.
When it is healthy, its core sticks out.\x
natdex_data0525_boldore.name: Boldore

natdex_data0526_gigalith.description:
The blasts of energy it makes from
sunbeams have terrifying power.
However, it's not able to fire its blasts
at night or on rainy days.\x
natdex_data0526_gigalith.name: Gigalith

natdex_data0527_woobat.description:
Its habitat is dark forests and caves.
Suction from its nostrils enables it
to stick to cave walls during sleep.
It leaves a heart-shaped mark behind.\x
natdex_data0527_woobat.name: Woobat

natdex_data0528_swoobat.description:
Anyone who comes into contact with
the ultrasonic waves emitted by a
courting male experiences a positive
mood shift.\x
natdex_data0528_swoobat.name: Swoobat

natdex_data0529_drilbur.description:
It can dig through the ground at a
speed of 30 mph by spinning its body.
It could give a car running aboveground
a good race.\x
natdex_data0529_drilbur.name: Drilbur

natdex_data0530_excadrill.description:
More than 300 feet below the surface,
they build mazelike nests. Their activity
can be destructive to subway tunnels,
but it can also help with construction.\x
natdex_data0530_excadrill.name: Excadrill

natdex_data0531_audino.description:
Its auditory sense is astounding.
Using the feelers on its ears, it can tell
how someone is feeling or when an egg
might hatch.
\x
natdex_data0531_audino.name: Audino

natdex_data0532_timburr.description:
These Pokémon appear at building
sites and help out with construction.
They always carry squared logs.
As they grow, they carry bigger logs.\x
natdex_data0532_timburr.name: Timburr

natdex_data0533_gurdurr.description:
They strengthen their bodies by carrying
steel beams. This Pokémon is so muscular
and strongly built that even a group of
wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.\x
natdex_data0533_gurdurr.name: Gurdurr

natdex_data0534_conkeldurr.description:
They use concrete pillars as walking
canes. Rather than rely solely on force,
they master moves that utilize the
centrifugal force of spinning concrete.\x
natdex_data0534_conkeldurr.name: Conkeldurr

natdex_data0535_tympole.description:
By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound
waves imperceptible to humans. It uses
the rhythm of these sounds to talk and
warns others of danger.\x
natdex_data0535_tympole.name: Tympole

natdex_data0536_palpitoad.description:
It lives in the water and on land.
When they vibrate the bumps on their
heads, they can make waves in water
or earthquake-like vibrations on land.\x
natdex_data0536_palpitoad.name: Palpitoad

natdex_data0537_seismitoad.description:
It increases the power of its punches
by vibrating the bumps on its fists.
They can also shoot paralyzing liquid
from their head bumps.\x
natdex_data0537_seismitoad.name: Seismitoad

natdex_data0538_throh.description:
When it tightens its belt, it becomes
stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave
their own belts. It changes belts as it
gets more powerful.\x
natdex_data0538_throh.name: Throh

natdex_data0539_sawk.description:
The sound of Sawk punching boulders
and trees can be heard all the way from
the mountains where they train.
Disturbing their training angers them.\x
natdex_data0539_sawk.name: Sawk

natdex_data0540_sewaddle.description:
It chews up leaves and sews them with
sticky thread extruded from its mouth.
Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes,
it is a mascot for fashion designers.\x
natdex_data0540_sewaddle.name: Sewaddle

natdex_data0541_swadloon.description:
Forests where Swadloon live have
superb foliage because the nutrients
they make from fallen leaves nourish
the plant life.\x
natdex_data0541_swadloon.name: Swadloon

natdex_data0542_leavanny.description:
It keeps its eggs warm with heat from
fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to
weave warm wrappings for Sewaddle by
using the silk secreted from its mouth.\x
natdex_data0542_leavanny.name: Leavanny

natdex_data0543_venipede.description:
Using the feelers on its head and tail,
it picks up vibrations in the air to
determine its prey's location and state.
It is brutally aggressive.\x
natdex_data0543_venipede.name: Venipede

natdex_data0544_whirlipede.description:
Storing energy for evolution, it sits.
But when attacked, it spins its body at
high speed like a wheel and then
crashes furiously into its opponent.\x
natdex_data0544_whirlipede.name: Whirlipede

natdex_data0545_scolipede.description:
With quick movements, it chases down
its foes, attacking relentlessly with its
horns until it prevails. Then it finishes
them off with deadly poison.\x
natdex_data0545_scolipede.name: Scolipede

natdex_data0546_cottonee.description:
When it finds others of its kind, they all
stick together. When enough of them
have collected, the mass resembles a
cumulonimbus cloud.\x
natdex_data0546_cottonee.name: Cottonee

natdex_data0547_whimsicott.description:
It rides on the wind and slips into
people's homes. After it has turned a
room into a cotton-filled mess, it giggles
to itself and takes off.\x
natdex_data0547_whimsicott.name: Whimsicott

natdex_data0548_petilil.description:
By pruning the leaves on its head with
regularity, this Pokémon can be grown
into a fine plump shape. These bitter
leaves refresh those who eat them.\x
natdex_data0548_petilil.name: Petilil

natdex_data0549_lilligant.description:
Even veteran Trainers face a challenge
in getting its beautiful flower to bloom.
It withers away if a trainer does not
take good care of it.\x
natdex_data0549_lilligant.name: Lilligant

natdex_data0550_basculin.description:
Red and blue Basculin usually do not
get along, but sometimes members of
one school mingle with the other's school.
These Pokémon are very hostile.\x
natdex_data0550_basculin.name: Basculin

natdex_data0551_sandile.description:
It conceals itself in the sand and
chomps down on the legs of any prey
that unwarily walk over it. Its favorite
food is Trapinch.\x
natdex_data0551_sandile.name: Sandile

natdex_data0552_krokorok.description:
They move in groups of a few individuals.
Thanks to the special membrane covering
its eyes, it can see its surroundings
clearly, even in the dead of night.\x
natdex_data0552_krokorok.name: Krokorok

natdex_data0553_krookodile.description:
Very violent Pokémon, they never allow
their prey to escape. Their jaws are so
powerful, they can crush the body of
an automobile.\x
natdex_data0553_krookodile.name: Krookodile

natdex_data0554_darumaka.description:
When its internal fire is burning, it
cannot calm down and it runs around.
When the fire diminishes, it pulls its
limbs into its body and falls asleep.\x
natdex_data0554_darumaka.name: Darumaka

natdex_data0555_darmanitan.description:
When one is injured in a fierce battle,
it transforms into a stone statue.
Then it meditates and sharpens its
mind and fights on mentally.\x
natdex_data0555_darmanitan.name: Darmanitan

natdex_data0556_maractus.description:
Arid regions are their habitat.
When it moves rhythmically, it makes a
sound similar to maracas, making the
surprised Pokémon flee.\x
natdex_data0556_maractus.name: Maractus

natdex_data0557_dwebble.description:
It makes a hole in a stone of a suitable
size. If that rock breaks, the Pokémon
remains agitated until it locates
a replacement.\x
natdex_data0557_dwebble.name: Dwebble

natdex_data0558_crustle.description:
Competing for territory, Crustle fight
viciously. The one whose boulder is
broken is the loser of the battle and
begins to weaken.\x
natdex_data0558_crustle.name: Crustle

natdex_data0559_scraggy.description:
Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it
can reduce damage by defensively
pulling its skin up to its neck.
Its skull is massively thick.\x
natdex_data0559_scraggy.name: Scraggy

natdex_data0560_scrafty.description:
Groups of them beat up anything that
enters their territory. The one with the
biggest crest is the group leader, and
is the most respected.\x
natdex_data0560_scrafty.name: Scrafty

natdex_data0561_sigilyph.description:
The guardians of an ancient city, they
always fly the same route while keeping
watch for invaders. They use their
psychic power to attack enemies.\x
natdex_data0561_sigilyph.name: Sigilyph

natdex_data0562_yamask.description:
These Pokémon arose from the spirits
of people interred in graves in past ages.
Each of them carries a mask that used
to be its face when it was human.\x
natdex_data0562_yamask.name: Yamask

natdex_data0563_cofagrigus.description:
Grave robbers who mistake them for
real coffins and get too close end up
trapped inside their bodies. Their bodies
are covered in pure gold.
\x
natdex_data0563_cofagrigus.name: Cofagrigus

natdex_data0564_tirtouga.description:
Reputed to be the ancestor of most
turtle Pokémon, it lived in warm seas
about a hundred million years ago.
It was restored from a fossil.\x
natdex_data0564_tirtouga.name: Tirtouga

natdex_data0565_carracosta.description:
They can live both in the ocean and
on land. Incredible jaw strength enables
them to chew up steel beams and rocks
along with their prey.\x
natdex_data0565_carracosta.name: Carracosta

natdex_data0566_archen.description:
Said to be the ancestor of all bird
Pokémon, Archen itself could not actually
fly but moved by hopping from treetop
to treetop.\x
natdex_data0566_archen.name: Archen

natdex_data0567_archeops.description:
They are intelligent and will cooperate
to catch prey. When one Archeops
had the prey cornered, another would
swoop on it.\x
natdex_data0567_archeops.name: Archeops

natdex_data0568_trubbish.description:
It gorges on trash until its stomach
is full. Then it belches toxic gas.
An unlucky whiff of this gas will put
a person in the hospital.\x
natdex_data0568_trubbish.name: Trubbish

natdex_data0569_garbodor.description:
Beware the poisonous liquid it shoots
from its right arm. If even a little of it
gets on you, you'll experience the full
effects of this unidentified toxin.\x
natdex_data0569_garbodor.name: Garbodor

natdex_data0570_zorua.description:
To protect themselves from danger, they
hide their true identities by transforming
into people and Pokémon. Apparently, it
often transforms into a silent child.\x
natdex_data0570_zorua.name: Zorua

natdex_data0571_zoroark.description:
Bonds between these Pokémon are very
strong. It protects the safety of its
pack by tricking its opponents. They
defend their lair with illusory scenery.\x
natdex_data0571_zoroark.name: Zoroark

natdex_data0572_minccino.description:
These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat.
They greet one another by rubbing each
other with their tails, which are always
kept well groomed and clean.\x
natdex_data0572_minccino.name: Minccino

natdex_data0573_cinccino.description:
Their white fur feels amazing to touch.
Cinccino's body is coated in a special
oil that repels dust and helps it deflect
attacks, such as punches.\x
natdex_data0573_cinccino.name: Cinccino

natdex_data0574_gothita.description:
They intently observe both Trainers and
Pokémon. Apparently, Gothita are looking
at something that only they can see. Their
ribbonlike feelers increase their power.\x
natdex_data0574_gothita.name: Gothita

natdex_data0575_gothorita.description:
Starlight is the source of their power.
They use hypnosis to control people and
Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading them
astray are told in every corner.\x
natdex_data0575_gothorita.name: Gothorita

natdex_data0576_gothitelle.description:
Starry skies thousands of light-years
away are visible in the space distorted by
their intense psychic power. When it learns
its Trainer's life span, it cries in sadness.\x
natdex_data0576_gothitelle.name: Gothitelle

natdex_data0577_solosis.description:
Because their bodies are enveloped
in a special liquid, they are fine in any
environment, no matter how severe. They
can use telepathy to talk with others.\x
natdex_data0577_solosis.name: Solosis

natdex_data0578_duosion.description:
When their brains, now divided in two,
are thinking the same thoughts,
these Pokémon exhibit their maximized
psychic power.\x
natdex_data0578_duosion.name: Duosion

natdex_data0579_reuniclus.description:
They use psychic power to control their
arms, which are made of a special liquid.
When Reuniclus shake hands, a network
forms between their brains.\x
natdex_data0579_reuniclus.name: Reuniclus

natdex_data0580_ducklett.description:
These bird Pokémon are excellent divers.
They are better at swimming than flying,
and they happily eat their favorite food,
peat moss, as they dive underwater.\x
natdex_data0580_ducklett.name: Ducklett

natdex_data0581_swanna.description:
Despite their elegant appearance, they
can flap their wings strongly and fly for
thousands of miles. The one in the middle
is the leader of the flock.\x
natdex_data0581_swanna.name: Swanna

natdex_data0582_vanillite.description:
The temperature of their breath is -58\h2AF.
They create snow crystals and make snow
fall in the areas around them. Vanillite is
treasured by households in warm regions.\x
natdex_data0582_vanillite.name: Vanillite

natdex_data0583_vanillish.description:
Vanillish has existed since the Ice Age.
It controls particles of ice, freezes its
opponents, and then shatters them with
a headbutt.\x
natdex_data0583_vanillish.name: Vanillish

natdex_data0584_vanilluxe.description:
Each of its two heads has a brain, and
when they are in agreement, it attacks
its enemies by exhaling a violent blizzard.
It makes snow clouds inside its body.\x
natdex_data0584_vanilluxe.name: Vanilluxe

natdex_data0585_deerling.description:
Their coloring changes according to the
seasons and can be slightly affected by
the temperature and humidity as well.
People use it to mark the seasons.\x
natdex_data0585_deerling.name: Deerling

natdex_data0586_sawsbuck.description:
Some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers
of spring because the plants growing on
its horns change according to the season.
The leader possesses magnificent horns.\x
natdex_data0586_sawsbuck.name: Sawsbuck

natdex_data0587_emolga.description:
It glides using its cape-like membrane.
It grills berries and bug Pokémon with
electric shocks from the pouches on its
cheeks and makes a meal of them.\x
natdex_data0587_emolga.name: Emolga

natdex_data0588_karrablast.description:
When they feel threatened, they spit an
acidic liquid to drive attackers away.
For some reason they evolve while they
are in the same place as Shelmet.\x
natdex_data0588_karrablast.name: Karrablast

natdex_data0589_escavalier.description:
Wearing the shell covering they stole
from Shelmet, they defend themselves and
attack with two lances. The steel armor
protects their whole body.\x
natdex_data0589_escavalier.name: Escavalier

natdex_data0590_foongus.description:
It lures Pokémon in with its pattern that
looks just like a Poké Ball, then releases
its poison spores. Why it resembles a
Poké Ball is unknown.\x
natdex_data0590_foongus.name: Foongus

natdex_data0591_amoonguss.description:
It lures prey close by dancing and waving
its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls,
in a swaying motion, but very few Pokémon
are fooled by this.\x
natdex_data0591_amoonguss.name: Amoonguss

natdex_data0592_frillish.description:
If its veil-like arms stun and wrap an
opponent, that foe will be dragged
five miles below the surface to its lair,
never to return.\x
natdex_data0592_frillish.name: Frillish

natdex_data0593_jellicent.description:
They propel themselves by expelling
absorbed seawater from their bodies.
It's said there's a castle of ships
Jellicent have sunk on the seafloor.\x
natdex_data0593_jellicent.name: Jellicent

natdex_data0594_alomomola.description:
When they find a wounded Pokémon,
they embrace it and bring it to shore.
The special membrane enveloping
Alomomola has the ability to heal wounds.\x
natdex_data0594_alomomola.name: Alomomola

natdex_data0595_joltik.description:
Since they can't generate their own
electricity, they attach themselves to
large-bodied Pokémon and absorb static
electricity, which they store in a pouch.\x
natdex_data0595_joltik.name: Joltik

natdex_data0596_galvantula.description:
It creates barriers from electrified silk
that stun foes. This works as a weapon as
well as a defense. While it is immobilized
by shock, they leisurely consume it.\x
natdex_data0596_galvantula.name: Galvantula

natdex_data0597_ferroseed.description:
It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock
while clinging to the ceiling of caves.
When threatened, it attacks by shooting
a barrage of spikes.\x
natdex_data0597_ferroseed.name: Ferroseed

natdex_data0598_ferrothorn.description:
It fights by swinging around its three
spiky feelers and shooting spikes.
A hit from these steel spikes can reduce
a boulder to rubble.\x
natdex_data0598_ferrothorn.name: Ferrothorn

natdex_data0599_klink.description:
Two bodies comprise a fixed pair.
The two minigears that mesh together
are predetermined. Each will rebound from
other minigears without meshing.\x
natdex_data0599_klink.name: Klink

natdex_data0600_klang.description:
A minigear and big gear comprise its
body. Spinning minigears are rotated
at high speed and repeatedly fired away.
It is dangerous if the gears don't return.\x
natdex_data0600_klang.name: Klang

natdex_data0601_klinklang.description:
Its red core functions as an energy tank.
It is rotated at high speed for a rapid
energy charge. It fires the charged energy
through its spikes into an area.\x
natdex_data0601_klinklang.name: Klinklang

natdex_data0602_tynamo.description:
These Pokémon move in schools.
One alone can emit only a trickle of
electricity, so a group of them gathers
to unleash a powerful electric shock.\x
natdex_data0602_tynamo.name: Tynamo

natdex_data0603_eelektrik.description:
These Pokémon have a big appetite.
It wraps itself around its prey and
paralyzes it with electricity from the
round spots on its sides. Then it chomps.\x
natdex_data0603_eelektrik.name: Eelektrik

natdex_data0604_eelektross.description:
They crawl out of the ocean using their
arms. They will attack prey on shore and
immediately drag it into the ocean, with
their sucker mouths.\x
natdex_data0604_eelektross.name: Eelektross

natdex_data0605_elgyem.description:
It psychically squeezes the brain of
its foe, causing unendurable headaches.
Rumors of its origin are linked to a UFO
crash site in the desert 50 years ago.\x
natdex_data0605_elgyem.name: Elgyem

natdex_data0606_beheeyem.description:
It can manipulate an opponent's memory.
Apparently, it communicates by flashing
its three fingers, but those patterns
haven't been decoded. \x
natdex_data0606_beheeyem.name: Beheeyem

natdex_data0607_litwick.description:
While Litwick shines a light and pretends
to be a guide, it absorbs the life force of
any who follow it, which becomes the fuel
that it burns.\x
natdex_data0607_litwick.name: Litwick

natdex_data0608_lampent.description:
This ominous Pokémon is feared.
Through cities it wanders, searching
for the spirits of the fallen. The spirits
it absorbs fuel its baleful fire.\x
natdex_data0608_lampent.name: Lampent

natdex_data0609_chandelure.description:
Being consumed in Chandelure's flame burns
up the spirit, leaving the body behind.
By waving the flames on its arms, it puts
its foes into a hypnotic trance.\x
natdex_data0609_chandelure.name: Chandelure

natdex_data0610_axew.description:
They mark their territory by leaving
gashes in trees with their tusks. If a
tusk breaks, a new one grows in quickly,
harder and sturdier than the last.\x
natdex_data0610_axew.name: Axew

natdex_data0611_fraxure.description:
Their tusks can shatter rocks.
A broken tusk will not grow back,
so it diligently sharpens its tusks on
river rocks after the end of a battle.\x
natdex_data0611_fraxure.name: Fraxure

natdex_data0612_haxorus.description:
They are kind but can be relentless
when defending territory. Their sturdy
tusks will stay sharp even if used to cut
steel beams.\x
natdex_data0612_haxorus.name: Haxorus

natdex_data0613_cubchoo.description:
Its nose is always running.
Their snot is a barometer of health.
When healthy, their snot is sticky and
the power of their ice moves increases.\x
natdex_data0613_cubchoo.name: Cubchoo

natdex_data0614_beartic.description:
It freezes its breath to create fangs
and claws of ice to fight with.
Very able in the water, it swims around
in northern seas and catches prey.\x
natdex_data0614_beartic.name: Beartic

natdex_data0615_cryogonal.description:
They are born in snow clouds. When
its body temperature goes up, it turns
into steam and vanishes. When its
temperature lowers, it returns to ice.\x
natdex_data0615_cryogonal.name: Cryogonal

natdex_data0616_shelmet.description:
When attacked, it defends itself by
closing the lid of its shell. It evolves
when bathed in an electric-like energy
along with Karrablast.\x
natdex_data0616_shelmet.name: Shelmet

natdex_data0617_accelgor.description:
When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to
prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in
layers of thin membrane. It is very light
and fights with ninja-like movements.\x
natdex_data0617_accelgor.name: Accelgor

natdex_data0618_stunfisk.description:
It conceals itself in the mud of the
seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch
it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.
It smiles when transmitting electricity.\x
natdex_data0618_stunfisk.name: Stunfisk

natdex_data0619_mienfoo.description:
They have mastered elegant combos.
As they concentrate, their battle moves
become swifter and more precise. What it
lacks in power, it makes up for in quantity.\x
natdex_data0619_mienfoo.name: Mienfoo

natdex_data0620_mienshao.description:
They use the long fur on their arms as
a whip to strike their opponents. Its arm
attacks come with such rapidity that they
cannot even be seen.\x
natdex_data0620_mienshao.name: Mienshao

natdex_data0621_druddigon.description:
It warms its body by absorbing sunlight
with its wings. When its body temperature
falls, it can no longer move. It uses its
sharp claws to catch prey.\x
natdex_data0621_druddigon.name: Druddigon

natdex_data0622_golett.description:
These Pokémon are thought to have
been created by the science of an
ancient and mysterious civilization.
It's been active for thousands of years.\x
natdex_data0622_golett.name: Golett

natdex_data0623_golurk.description:
Golurk were created to protect people
and Pokémon by an ancient civilisation.
Removing the seal on its chest makes its
internal energy go out of control.\x
natdex_data0623_golurk.name: Golurk

natdex_data0624_pawniard.description:
Ignoring their injuries, groups attack by
sinking the blades that cover their bodies
into their prey. If battling dulls them, it
sharpens them on stones by the river.\x
natdex_data0624_pawniard.name: Pawniard

natdex_data0625_bisharp.description:
This pitiless Pokémon commands a group
of Pawniard to hound prey into immobility.
It battles to become the boss, but will be
driven from the group if it loses.\x
natdex_data0625_bisharp.name: Bisharp

natdex_data0626_bouffalant.description:
Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even
if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.
Their headbutts have enough destructive
force to derail a train.\x
natdex_data0626_bouffalant.name: Bouffalant

natdex_data0627_rufflet.description:
With its sharp claws, this Pokémon pierces
its prey, and then it pecks at them.
Although it also consumes berries, it's a
carnivore at heart.\x
natdex_data0627_rufflet.name: Rufflet

natdex_data0628_braviary.description:
For the sake of its friends, this brave
warrior of the sky will not stop battling,
even if it is injured. One can carry a car
while flying.\x
natdex_data0628_braviary.name: Braviary

natdex_data0629_vullaby.description:
It can't fly yet and must wait until its
wings have developed more. They guard
their posteriors with bones that were
gathered by Mandibuzz.\x
natdex_data0629_vullaby.name: Vullaby

natdex_data0630_mandibuzz.description:
They adorn themselves beautifully with
bones. This is supposedly an effort to
attract males, but no male Mandibuzz
have ever been found.\x
natdex_data0630_mandibuzz.name: Mandibuzz

natdex_data0631_heatmor.description:
It draws in air through its tail, transforms
it into fire, and uses it like a tongue.
They burn through Durant's steel bodies
and consume their insides.\x
natdex_data0631_heatmor.name: Heatmor

natdex_data0632_durant.description:
Durant dig nests in mountains.
Individuals each play different roles in
driving Heatmor, their natural predator,
away from their colony.\x
natdex_data0632_durant.name: Durant

natdex_data0633_deino.description:
Lacking sight, it's unaware of its
surroundings, so it bumps into things and
eats anything that moves. Approaching
it carelessly is dangerous.\x
natdex_data0633_deino.name: Deino

natdex_data0634_zweilous.description:
After it has eaten up all the food in its
territory, it moves on to another area.
Whichever head eats more than the other
gets to be the leader.\x
natdex_data0634_zweilous.name: Zweilous

natdex_data0635_hydreigon.description:
This brutal Pokémon travels the skies on
its six wings. The heads on their arms do
not have brains. They use all three heads
to consume and destroy everything.\x
natdex_data0635_hydreigon.name: Hydreigon

natdex_data0636_larvesta.description:
This Pokémon was believed to have
been born from the sun. It spews fire from
its horns and encases itself in a cocoon
of fire when it evolves.\x
natdex_data0636_larvesta.name: Larvesta

natdex_data0637_volcarona.description:
When volcanic ash darkened the
atmosphere, it appeared and saved Pokémon
from freezing, Volcarona's fire provided a
replacement for the sun.\x
natdex_data0637_volcarona.name: Volcarona

natdex_data0638_cobalion.description:
It has a body and heart of steel. This
legendary Pokémon battled against humans
to protect Pokémon. Its personality
is calm and composed.\x
natdex_data0638_cobalion.name: Cobalion

natdex_data0639_terrakion.description:
Spoken of in legend, this Pokémon used
its phenomenal power to destroy a castle
in its effort to protect Pokémon that had
lost their homes in a war among humans.\x
natdex_data0639_terrakion.name: Terrakion

natdex_data0640_virizion.description:
Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades.
Legends say this Pokémon used
whirlwind-like movements to confound
and swiftly cut its opponents.\x
natdex_data0640_virizion.name: Virizion

natdex_data0641_tornadus.description:
Tornadus expels massive energy from
its tail, causing severe storms.
Its power can blow entire houses away.
It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.\x
natdex_data0641_tornadus.name: Tornadus

natdex_data0642_thundurus.description:
The spikes on its tail discharge immense
bolts of lightning. Countless charred
remains mar the landscape of places
through which Thundurus has passed.\x
natdex_data0642_thundurus.name: Thundurus

natdex_data0643_reshiram.description:
This Pokémon appears in legends. It
sends flames into the air from its tail,
burning up everything around it. It helps
those who want to build a world of truth.\x
natdex_data0643_reshiram.name: Reshiram

natdex_data0644_zekrom.description:
This legendary Pokémon can scorch the
world with lightning. It has a generator
that creates electricity in its tail. It
assists those with strong ideals.\x
natdex_data0644_zekrom.name: Zekrom

natdex_data0645_landorus.description:
The energy that comes pouring from its tail
increases the nutrition in the soil, making
crops grow to great size. It has been
hailed as ["]The Guardian of the Fields."\x
natdex_data0645_landorus.name: Landorus

natdex_data0646_kyurem.description:
This legendary ice Pokémon waits for a
hero to fill in the missing parts of its
body with truth or ideals. Its body became
frozen when its energy leaked out.\x
natdex_data0646_kyurem.name: Kyurem

natdex_data0647_keldeo.description:
When it is resolute, its body fills with
power and it becomes swifter. It crosses
the world, running over the surfaces of
oceans and rivers.\x
natdex_data0647_keldeo.name: Keldeo

natdex_data0648_meloetta.description:
The melodies sung by Meloetta have the
power to make Pokémon that hear them
happy or sad. Many famous songs have been
inspired by the tunes that Meloetta plays.\x
natdex_data0648_meloetta.name: Meloetta

natdex_data0649_genesect.description:
Over 300 million years ago, it was
feared as the strongest of hunters.
Team Plasma altered it and attached
a cannon to its back.\x
natdex_data0649_genesect.name: Genesect

natdex_data0650_chespin.description:
The quills on its head are usually soft.
When it flexes them, the points become
so hard and sharp that they can pierce
rock without any effort.\x
natdex_data0650_chespin.name: Chespin

natdex_data0651_quilladin.description:
They strengthen the sturdy shell covering
their bodies by running into one another.
They are very kind and won't start fights,
but will counterattack with sharp quills.\x
natdex_data0651_quilladin.name: Quilladin

natdex_data0652_chesnaught.description:
It shields its allies from danger with
its own body. When it takes a defensive
posture with its fists guarding its face,
it can withstand a bomb blast.\x
natdex_data0652_chesnaught.name: Chesnaught

natdex_data0653_fennekin.description:
As it walks, it munches on a twig to fill
itself with energy in place of a snack.
It intimidates opponents by puffing hot
air out of its roomy ears.\x
natdex_data0653_fennekin.name: Fennekin

natdex_data0654_braixen.description:
Braixen has a twig stuck in its tail.
When the twig is plucked from its tail,
friction sets the twig alight. The flame
is used to send signals to its allies.\x
natdex_data0654_braixen.name: Braixen

natdex_data0655_delphox.description:
It gazes into the flame at the tip of its
branch to achieve a focused state, which
allows it to see into the future. It uses
psychic power to incinerate its foes.\x
natdex_data0655_delphox.name: Delphox

natdex_data0656_froakie.description:
It protects its skin by covering its body
in bubbles it secretes from its chest and
back. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it
keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.\x
natdex_data0656_froakie.name: Froakie

natdex_data0657_frogadier.description:
It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with
precise control, hitting empty cans up to
a hundred feet away. Frogadier's swiftness
is unparalleled.\x
natdex_data0657_frogadier.name: Frogadier

natdex_data0658_greninja.description:
It appears and vanishes with a ninja's
grace. It toys with its enemies using swift
movements, while slicing them with throwing
stars made of compressed water.\x
natdex_data0658_greninja.name: Greninja

natdex_data0659_bunnelby.description:
It has ears like shovels. Digging holes
strengthens its ears so much that they
can sever thick roots effortlessly.
Bunnelby dig the whole night through.\x
natdex_data0659_bunnelby.name: Bunnelby

natdex_data0660_diggersby.description:
With its powerful ears it reduces dense
bedrock to rubble. It can be a big help
at construction sites. When it's finished
digging, it lounges about lazily.\x
natdex_data0660_diggersby.name: Diggersby

natdex_data0661_fletchling.description:
This amiable Pokémon is easy to train.
But when battle is joined, it shows its
ferocious side. It's merciless to
intruders that enter its territory.\x
natdex_data0661_fletchling.name: Fletchling

natdex_data0662_fletchindr.description:
From its beak, it expels embers that set
the tall grass on fire. Then it pounces on
any bewildered Pokémon that pop out of
the grass.\x
natdex_data0662_fletchindr.name: Fletchindr

natdex_data0663_talonflame.description:
In the fever of an exciting battle, it
showers embers from the gaps between its
feathers and takes to the air. It finishes
its prey off with a colossal kick.\x
natdex_data0663_talonflame.name: Talonflame

natdex_data0664_scatterbug.description:
When under attack from bird Pokémon,
it spews a poisonous black powder that
causes paralysis on contact. Scatterbug
can live in any region or climate.\x
natdex_data0664_scatterbug.name: Scatterbug

natdex_data0665_spewpa.description:
It lives hidden within thicket shadows.
When predators attack, it quickly bristles
the fur covering its body in an effort to
threaten them.\x
natdex_data0665_spewpa.name: Spewpa

natdex_data0666_vivillon.description:
Vivillon with many different patterns are
found all over the world. These patterns
are affected by the climate of their
habitat. It scatters colorful scales.\x
natdex_data0666_vivillon.name: Vivillon

natdex_data0667_litleo.description:
They set off on their own from their pride
and live by themselves to become stronger.
These hot-blooded Pokémon are quick
to start a fight.\x
natdex_data0667_litleo.name: Litleo

natdex_data0668_pyroar.description:
The male with the largest mane of fire
is the leader of the pride. The females
protect the pride's cubs. They viciously
threaten any challenger.\x
natdex_data0668_pyroar.name: Pyroar

natdex_data0669_flabebe.description:
When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells
on that flower its whole life long.
It floats on the wind's embrace with
an untroubled heart.\x
natdex_data0669_flabebe.name: Flabébé

natdex_data0670_floette.description:
When the flowers of a well-tended flower
bed bloom, it appears and celebrates
with an elegant dance. It draws out the
power of flowers to battle.\x
natdex_data0670_floette.name: Floette

natdex_data0671_florges.description:
It claims exquisite flower gardens as its
territory. In times long past, governors of
castles would invite Florges to create
gardens to embellish the castle domains.\x
natdex_data0671_florges.name: Florges

natdex_data0672_skiddo.description:
If it has sunshine and water, it doesn't
need to eat, because it can generate
energy from the leaves on its back.
It has a placid disposition.\x
natdex_data0672_skiddo.name: Skiddo

natdex_data0673_gogoat.description:
It can tell how its trainer is feeling by
subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This
empathetic sense lets them run as if one
being. They inhabit mountainous regions.\x
natdex_data0673_gogoat.name: Gogoat

natdex_data0674_pancham.description:
There's no point to the leaf in its mouth,
aside from an effort to look cool. It's
mischievous, so it's not well suited to
inexperienced Trainers.\x
natdex_data0674_pancham.name: Pancham

natdex_data0675_pangoro.description:
It boasts superb physical strength.
Those who wish to become Pangoro's
Trainer have no choice but to converse
with their fists.\x
natdex_data0675_pangoro.name: Pangoro

natdex_data0676_furfrou.description:
Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes
it more elegant but also increases the
swiftness of its movements. These
Pokémon were the guardians of kings.\x
natdex_data0676_furfrou.name: Furfrou

natdex_data0677_espurr.description:
It has enough psychic energy to blast
everything within 300 feet of itself.
The organ that emits its intense psychic
power is sheltered by its ears.\x
natdex_data0677_espurr.name: Espurr

natdex_data0678_meowstic.description:
The eyeball patterns on the interior of
its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the
patterns tightly covered because that
power is too immense.\x
natdex_data0678_meowstic.name: Meowstic

natdex_data0679_honedge.description:
If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it
wraps a blue cloth around that person's
arm and drains that person's life
energy completely.\x
natdex_data0679_honedge.name: Honedge

natdex_data0680_doublade.description:
When Honedge evolves, it divides into
two swords. The complex attack patterns
of its two swords are unstoppable, even
against those skilled at swordplay.\x
natdex_data0680_doublade.name: Doublade

natdex_data0681_aegislash.description:
Generations of kings were attended to
by these Pokémon, which used their
spectral power to manipulate and control
people and Pokémon.\x
natdex_data0681_aegislash.name: Aegislash

natdex_data0682_spritzee.description:
In the past, rather than using perfume,
royal ladies carried a Spritzee that would
waft a fragrance they liked. Its fragrance
changes depending on what it has eaten.\x
natdex_data0682_spritzee.name: Spritzee

natdex_data0683_aromatisse.description:
Its scent is so overpowering that,
unless a Trainer happens to really enjoy
the smell, he or she will have a hard time
walking alongside it.\x
natdex_data0683_aromatisse.name: Aromatisse

natdex_data0684_swirlix.description:
Because it eats nothing but sweets, its
fur is as sticky sweet as cotton candy.
To entangle its opponents in battle, it
extrudes sticky white threads.\x
natdex_data0684_swirlix.name: Swirlix

natdex_data0685_slurpuff.description:
Slurpuff can distinguish even the
faintest of scents. It puts its sensitive
sense of smell to use by helping pastry
chefs in their work.\x
natdex_data0685_slurpuff.name: Slurpuff

natdex_data0686_inkay.description:
It flashes the light-emitting spots on its
body, which drains its opponent's will
to fight. It takes the opportunity to
scuttle away and hide.\x
natdex_data0686_inkay.name: Inkay

natdex_data0687_malamar.description:
It lures prey close with hypnotic motions,
then wraps its tentacles around it before
finishing it off with digestive fluids. It
forces others to do whatever it wants.\x
natdex_data0687_malamar.name: Malamar

natdex_data0688_binacle.description:
They stretch and then contract, yanking
their rocks along with them in bold hops.
They eat seaweed that washes up on
the shoreline.\x
natdex_data0688_binacle.name: Binacle

natdex_data0689_barbaracle.description:
Barbaracle's legs and hands have minds
of their own, and they will move
independently. But they usually follow
the head's orders.\x
natdex_data0689_barbaracle.name: Barbaracle

natdex_data0690_skrelp.description:
Camouflaged as rotten kelp, it hides
from foes while storing up power for its
evolution. They spray liquid poison on
prey that approach unawares.\x
natdex_data0690_skrelp.name: Skrelp

natdex_data0691_dragalge.description:
Their poison is strong enough to eat
through the hull of a tanker. Tales are
told of ships that wander into seas where
Dragalge live, never to return.\x
natdex_data0691_dragalge.name: Dragalge

natdex_data0692_clauncher.description:
Through controlled expulsions of internal
gas, it can expel water like a pistol shot.
At close distances, it can even shatter
large rocks.\x
natdex_data0692_clauncher.name: Clauncher

natdex_data0693_clawitzer.description:
By expelling water from the nozzle in the
back of its enormous claw, it can move
at a speed of 60 knots. They launch
cannonballs made of water.\x
natdex_data0693_clawitzer.name: Clawitzer

natdex_data0694_helioptile.description:
They make their home in deserts.
They can generate their own energy from
basking in the sun, so eating food is not
a requirement.\x
natdex_data0694_helioptile.name: Helioptile

natdex_data0695_heliolisk.description:
A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient
electricity to power a skyscraper. It can
stimulate its muscles with electricity,
boosting the strength in its legs.\x
natdex_data0695_heliolisk.name: Heliolisk

natdex_data0696_tyrunt.description:
Its immense jaws have enough destructive
force that it can chew up a car. If
something happens that it doesn't like,
it throws a tantrum and runs wild.\x
natdex_data0696_tyrunt.name: Tyrunt

natdex_data0697_tyrantrum.description:
Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could
shred thick metal plates as if they were
paper, it was invincible in the ancient
world it once inhabited.\x
natdex_data0697_tyrantrum.name: Tyrantrum

natdex_data0698_amaura.description:
This ancient Pokémon was restored from
part of its body that had been frozen in
ice for over 100 million years. It lived in a
cold land where there were no predators.\x
natdex_data0698_amaura.name: Amaura

natdex_data0699_aurorus.description:
Using the diamond-shaped crystals on its
body it can instantly create a wall of ice
to block an opponent's attack, or encase
them in ice.\x
natdex_data0699_aurorus.name: Aurorus

natdex_data0700_sylveon.description:
Its ribbonlike feelers give off an aura
that weakens hostility in its prey, causing
them to let down their guard. A moment
later, it pounces.\x
natdex_data0700_sylveon.name: Sylveon

natdex_data0701_hawlucha.description:
With its wings, it controls its position in
the air. Its proficient fighting skills
enable it to keep up with big bruisers
like Machamp and Hariyama.\x
natdex_data0701_hawlucha.name: Hawlucha

natdex_data0702_dedenne.description:
Its whiskers serve as antennas.
By sending and receiving electrical
waves, it can communicate with others
over vast distances.\x
natdex_data0702_dedenne.name: Dedenne

natdex_data0703_carbink.description:
Born from the high temperatures and
pressures deep underground, it defends
itself by firing beams from the jewel part
of its body.\x
natdex_data0703_carbink.name: Carbink

natdex_data0704_goomy.description:
Its source of protection is its slimy,
germ-laden mucous membrane. Anyone
who touches it will need some thorough
hand-washing.\x
natdex_data0704_goomy.name: Goomy

natdex_data0705_sliggoo.description:
This Pokémon's mucous can dissolve
anything. Toothless, it sprays mucous
on its prey. Once they're nicely dissolved,
it slurps them up.\x
natdex_data0705_sliggoo.name: Sliggoo

natdex_data0706_goodra.description:
It gets picked on because it's meek.
But then, whoever teased it gets to feel
the full force of its horns and a good
swatting from its thick tail.\x
natdex_data0706_goodra.name: Goodra

natdex_data0707_klefki.description:
These key collectors threaten any
attackers by fiercely jingling their keys
at them. It will sneak into people's homes
to steal their keys.\x
natdex_data0707_klefki.name: Klefki

natdex_data0708_phantump.description:
According to legend, medicine to cure
any illness can be made by plucking the
green leaves on its head, brewing them,
and boiling down the liquid.\x
natdex_data0708_phantump.name: Phantump

natdex_data0709_trevenant.description:
Through its roots, it exerts control over
other trees. A deadly curse falls upon
anyone cutting down trees in forests
where Trevenant dwell.
\x
natdex_data0709_trevenant.name: Trevenant

natdex_data0710_pumpkaboo.description:
It is said to carry wandering spirits to
the place where they belong so they can
move on. As the sun sets, it becomes
restless and active.
\x
natdex_data0710_pumpkaboo.name: Pumpkaboo

natdex_data0711_gourgeist.description:
Singing in eerie voices, they wander town
streets on the night of the new moon.
Anyone who hears their song will become
inflicted with a curse.\x
natdex_data0711_gourgeist.name: Gourgeist

natdex_data0712_bergmite.description:
It blocks opponents' attacks with the ice
that shields its body. It uses cold air to
repair any cracks with new ice. They live
in herds on snowy mountains.\x
natdex_data0712_bergmite.name: Bergmite

natdex_data0713_avalugg.description:
The way several Bergmite huddle on its
back make it look like an aircraft carrier
made of ice. Its cumbersome frame crushes
anything that stands in its way.\x
natdex_data0713_avalugg.name: Avalugg

natdex_data0714_noibat.description:
They live in pitch-black caves. Even a
robust wrestler will become dizzy and
unable to stand when exposed to its
200,000-hertz ultrasonic waves.\x
natdex_data0714_noibat.name: Noibat

natdex_data0715_noivern.description:
They fly around on moonless nights and
attack careless prey. The ultrasonic waves
it emits from its ears can reduce a large
boulder to pebbles.\x
natdex_data0715_noivern.name: Noivern

natdex_data0716_xerneas.description:
Legends say that when the horns on
its head shine in seven colors, it is
sharing everlasting life. It slept for a
thousand years in the form of a tree\x
natdex_data0716_xerneas.name: Xerneas

natdex_data0717_yveltal.description:
When its life comes to an end, its wings
and tail spread wide and glow red, and
it absorbs the life energy of every living
thing and turns into a cocoon.\x
natdex_data0717_yveltal.name: Yveltal

natdex_data0718_zygarde.description:
It's said to be monitoring the ecosystem
from deep in the caves where it lives.
There are rumors that even greater power
lies hidden within its cells.\x
natdex_data0718_zygarde.name: Zygarde

natdex_data0719_diancie.description:
A sudden transformation of Carbink,
its pink, glimmering body is said to be
the loveliest sight in the whole world.
It creates diamonds between its hands.\x
natdex_data0719_diancie.name: Diancie

natdex_data0720_hoopa.description:
In its true form, it possess a huge amount
of power. When its powers are sealed away,
it is transformed into a much smaller form.
It teleports things to a secret place.\x
natdex_data0720_hoopa.name: Hoopa

natdex_data0721_volcanion.description:
It lets out billows of steam from the arms
on its back and disappears into the dense
fog. It's said to live in mountains where
humans do not tread.\x
natdex_data0721_volcanion.name: Volcanion

natdex_data0722_rowlet.description:
This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis
to store up energy during the day, while
becoming active at night. Silently it
glides, drawing near to its target.\x
natdex_data0722_rowlet.name: Rowlet

natdex_data0723_dartrix.description:
A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time
preening its wings. Its preoccupation
with any dirt on its plumage can leave
it unable to battle.\x
natdex_data0723_dartrix.name: Dartrix

natdex_data0724_decidueye.description:
Decidueye is cool and cautious.
It fires arrow quills from its wings with
such precision, they can pierce a pebble
at distances of over a hundred yards.\x
